(3798, 276, 'trip_itinerary', '<strong>Day 01:</strong> Arrival in Kathmandu Airport (1,350 m), meet our staff then transfers to hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 02:</strong> Drive to Pokhara (820 m) by Tourist bus approx 6/7 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 03:</strong> Drive to Naya Pul (1,070 m) by Tourist bus to (1 hour) and to Tikhe Dhunga (1,540 m) approx 3-4 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 04:</strong> Trek to Ghorepani (2,750 m) approx 5-6 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 05:</strong> Climb Ghorepani to Poon Hill (3,210 m) where you will lots enjoys for sunrise view with other many mountains Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Niligiri North, Central, South, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Hiunchuli, Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre, Lamjuung Mimal and other many peaks back to Ghorepani and trek continue to Tadapani (2,590 m) approx 6-7 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 06:</strong> Trek to Chhomrong village (2, 170 m) approx. 5 hrs where Gurung communities showing the welcome cultural dense for the guest\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 07:</strong> Trek to Himalaya Hotel (2,790 m) approx. 5-6 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 08:</strong> Trek to Annapurna Base Camp (4,130 m) approx. 6 hours via Deurali, Machhapuchhare Base Camp (3,700 m) and trek continue to Annapurna Base Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 09:</strong> Trek to Dovan (2,505 m) – Sinuwa (2,340 m) approx. 6-7 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 10:</strong> Trek to Jhinu Danda (1,780 m) approx. 4 hours, (where you will lots relax hot bath with Natural Hot Spring) at Jhinu-Modi Kola back to Jhinu Danda\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 11:</strong> Trek to Pothana (1,900 m) approx. 6 hrs via Landruk (1,565 m), Tolka (1,700 m), Bhickok Deurali (2,100 m) and trek continue to Pothana\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 12:</strong> Trek to Phedi (1,130 m) approx. 2-3 hours via Dhampus (1,650 m),  Phedi and drive to Pokhara (8,20 m) and transfer to hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 13:</strong> Next day early in the morning drive to Sarangkot (1,592 m) you will enjoys for the best sunrise with mountain views Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre and other many Peaks<strong>.</strong> Back to hotel and Pokhara City Sightseeing visit of Cave, Buddhist Monastery, and World Peace Stupas (Chorten).\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 14:</strong> Drive to Kathmandu, transfers to hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 15:</strong> Free day in Kathmandu for rest and shopping\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 16:</strong> Transfer to international airport for your final departure (Trip ends.)'),
