(7350, 455, 'trip_itinerary', '<strong>Day 01:</strong> Arrival in Kathmandu airport, (1,350 m) meet our staff and transfer to hotel\r\n<strong>Day 02:</strong> Drive to Pokhara (8,20 m) by Tourist bus approx 6/7 hours\r\n<strong>Day 03:</strong> Drive to Naya Pul (1,070 m) by Tourist bus to (1 hour) and to Tikhe Dhunga (1,540 m) approx 3/4 hours<strong>\r\nDay 04:</strong> Trek Tikhe Dhunga to Ghorepani (2,750 m) approx 5/6 hours\r\n<strong>Day 05:</strong> Climb Ghorepani to Poon Hill (3,210 m) where you will lots enjoys for the sunrise view with other many mountains Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Niligiri North, Central, South, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Hiunchuli, Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre, Lamjuung Mimal and other many peaks back to Ghorepani and continue trek to Tatopani (1,190 m) approx 5/6 hours, (where you will lots relax hot bath with Natural Hot Spring in Tatopani)\r\n<strong>Day 06:</strong> Trek to Ghasa (2,010 m) approx 5 hours\r\n<strong>Day 07:</strong> Trek to Marpha village (2,670 m) approx 7 hours, where you will have lots of Excursion Buddhist Monastery, Mani wall and Stupas (Chortens) at Marpha village\r\n<strong>Day 08:</strong> Trek to Jomsom (2,710 m) approx 3/4 hour\r\n<strong>Day 09:</strong> Trek to Kagbeni (2,800 m) approx 4/5 hours you will have in the evening to visit Buddhist Monastery at Kagbeni\r\n<strong>Day 10:</strong> Trek to Muktinath (3,800 m) approx 3-4 hours where you will have lots of Excursion Buddhist Monastery, Stupas (Chortens), Mani wall &amp; Hindus Temple at Muktinath\r\n<strong>Day 11:</strong> Trek back to Jomsom (2,710 m) approx 5 hours by walk, where you have a option by walk, Jeep or by Mountain Bike to Jomsom\r\n<strong>Day 12:</strong> Fly back to Pokhara (8,20 m) (Approx 25minis) transfers to hotel free day in Pokhara\r\n<strong>Day 13:</strong> Next day early in the morning drive to Sarangkot (1,592 m) you will enjoys for the best sunrise with mountain views Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre and other many Peaks<strong>.</strong> Back to hotel and Pokhara City Sightseeing visit of Cave, Buddhist Monastery, and World Peace Stupas (Chorten).\r\n<strong>Day 14:</strong> Drive to Kathmandu, transfers to hotel\r\n<strong>Day 15:</strong> Free day in Kathmandu for rest and shopping\r\n<strong>Day 16:</strong> Transfer to international airport for your final departure (Trip ends.)'),
