(10372, 584, 'trip_itinerary', '<strong>Day 01:</strong> Arrive in Kathmandu (1,350 m) &amp; transfer to Hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 02:</strong> Drive to Beshi Shahar (760 m) by Tourist bus approx 6/7 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 03:</strong> Trek to Chamje (1,430 m) approx 6 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 04:</strong> Trek to Tal (1,700 m) approx 5 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 05:</strong> Trek to Chame (2670 m) approx 6 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 06</strong>: Trek to Lower Pisang (3,200 m) approx 5 hours and here you will have to visit Buddhists Monastery, Stupas (Chortens) at Upper Pisang Village (3,300 m)\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 07:</strong> Trek to Manang village (3,540 m) approx 5 hours and on the way at Humde (3,280 m) where you will have to visit beautiful Buddhists Monastery and a wonderful mountains views you then you are continue trek to Manang village\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 08:</strong> Rest and acclimatization day in Manang village..! The rest of day we will walk around Manang village and Upper Manang village where we will a lots of enjoy with a beautiful Buddhists Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens), Mani wall we will also enjoys wonderful mountains views and Manang Lake we will walk to Lakeside near Manang village (3,540 m)\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 09:</strong> Trek to Letdar (4,200 m) approx 4 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 10:</strong> Trek to Thorung La High Camp (4,570 m) approx 3 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 11:</strong> Cross from High Camp early in the marooning we start to cross over Thorung La Pass (5,416 m) and trek continue to Muktinath (3,800 m) approx 8-9 hours in the evening you will visit to Buddhists Monasteries to around Muktinath\r\n<strong>Day 12:</strong> Trek to Marpha (2,670 m) approx 6/7 hours by walk, where you have a option by walk, Jeep or by Mountain Bike to Marpha\r\n<strong>Day 13:</strong> Excursion Buddhist Monastery and Stupa in Marpha village and drive by Local bus to Tatopani (1,190 m), where you will enjoying lots with the hot bath (Natural Hot Spring)\r\n<strong>Day 14:</strong> Trek to Ghorepani (2750 m) approximately time 6/7 hours\r\n<strong>Day 15:</strong> Get up early in the morning climb to Poon Hill (3,210m) 1/2 hrs climbing) you will enjoys for the best sunrise with mountain views &amp; back to Ghorepani for breakfast and trek continue to Tadapani (2,660 m) approx 7/8 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 16:</strong> Trek to Ghandruk village (2,030) approx 4 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 17:</strong> Trek to Naya Pul (1070m.) and same day drive to Pokhara (850 m), you will 4 hours walking and 1 hours driving) via Naya Pul\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 18:</strong> Drive from Pokhara (850 m) to Kathmandu (1,350 m) approx 7/8 hours &amp; transfer to Hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 19:</strong> Day reserved for optional activities\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 20:</strong> Transfer to international airport for your final departure (Trip ends.)'),
