(15647, 1008, 'trip_itinerary', '<strong>Day 01:</strong> Arrive in Kathmandu (1,350 m) &amp; transfer to Hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 02:</strong> Drive to Jagat by Pazero Jeep (1,300 m) via Beshishahar (760 m) / Bhulbhule (840 m) / Syange (1100 m) approx. 09-10 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 03:</strong> Trek to Dharapani (1860m.) approx. 5/6 hours, on the way you can enjoys for many beautiful waterfalls\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 04:</strong> Trek to Chame (2670m.) approx. 5/6 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 05</strong>: Trek to Lower Pisang (3,200 m) approx 5 hours and here you will have to visit Buddhists Monastery, Stupas (Chortens) at Lower Pisang and Upper Pisang Village (3,300 m)\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 06:</strong> Trek to Manang village (3,540 m) approx 5 hours, here we flow real trekking route from Upper Pisang (3,300 m), Ghyaru village (3,670 m), Nawal village (3,660 m) and Bhraka (3,360 m) where you will have real enjoys with beautiful and very older Buddhist Monasteries, Houses and other many with a wonderful mountains view you can see, then our trek continue to Manang village\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 07:</strong> Rest and acclimatization day in Manang village..! The rest day we will walk around Manang village and Upper Manang village where we will lots of enjoys with a beautiful Buddhist Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall. Also we will enjoys wonderful mountains view and we will walk to Lakeside near Manang village (3,540 m)\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 08: </strong>Trek to Khangsar village (3,734 m) approx 4/5 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 09:</strong> Trek to Tilicho Lake (4920m) approx 5 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 10: </strong>Trek to Khangsar village (3,700 m) approx 6 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 11:</strong> Trek to Letdar (4,200 m) approx 5/6 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 12:</strong> Trek to Thorung La High Camp (4,570 m) approx 3 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 13:</strong> We start our trip early in the morning from Thorung La High Camp we cross over Thorung La Pass (5,416 m) and Trek Continue to Muktinath (3,800 m) approx 8/9 hours in the evening where we will visit and enjoys with 108 water spouts flowing holy water from taps and mysterious natural gas fires that surprises peoples believe blessed by <strong>Guru Rinpoche’s (Guru Padma Sambhava) </strong>and we will visit Buddhists Monastery, Stupas (Chortens), Mani wall and Hindu Temple\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 14:</strong> Trek to Jomsom (2,710 m) approx 5 hours Option by walk, Jeep or by Mountain Bike to Jomsom\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 15:</strong> Trek to Marpha Village (2,670 m) approx 5 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 16:</strong> Excursion Buddhist Monastery, Stupa (Chortens) and Mani wall at Marpha village and drive by Local bus via Ghasa Tatopani (1,190 m) where you will lots of enjoys with hot bath by (Natural Hot Spring)\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 17:</strong> Drive to Pokhara (820 m) by tourist bus approx 3 hours free day in Pokhara\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 18:</strong> Next day early in the morning drive to Sarangkot (1,592 m) you will enjoys for the best sunrise with mountain views Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre and other many Peaks<strong>.</strong> Back to hotel and Pokhara City Sightseeing visit of Cave, Buddhist Monastery, and World Peace Stupas (Chorten).\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 19:</strong> Drive to Kathmandu, transfers to hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 20:</strong> Free day in Kathmandu for rest and shopping\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 21:</strong> Transfer to international airport for your final departure (Trip ends.)\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>'),
