(17960, 1042, 'trip_itinerary', '<strong>Day 01:</strong> Arrival in Kathmandu (1350 m) airport, transfer to hotel overnight at hotel Kathmandu.\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 02:</strong> Drive to Pokhara (820 m) transfer to hotel 200kms/7 hours. Evening leisure at Fewa Lake overnight at hotel pokhara\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 03:</strong> Drive to Pokhara (820 m) transfer to hotel 200kms/7 hours. Evening leisure at Fewa Lake overnight at hotel pokhara\r\n\r\n<strong>Day04: </strong>Moring Fly to Jomsom (2710 m) and same day trek to Kagbeni (2800 m) approx 3/4 hours evening Buddhist monastery excursion at Kagbeni. Overnight at Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 05:</strong> Trek Kagbeni to Samar (3620 m approx 7 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\nThis day after breakfast we start our trek to Samar.\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 06:</strong> Trek Samar to Ghiling (3570 m) approx 7 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 07: </strong>Trek Ghiling to Tsarang (3560 m) approx 6 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 08: </strong>Rest day at Tsarang Buddhists Monastery and Stupa Sightseeing\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 09:</strong> Trek Tsarang to Lo Manthang (3840 m) approx 6 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 10:</strong> Rest day in Lo Manthang we walk full day around Garpho (3897 m) Buddhists Monastery Sightseeing and walk to Cave back to Lo Manthang O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 11:</strong> Trek Lo Manthang to Ghami (3510 m) via Marang (Chgo) La (4230 m), Ghar Gumba (3920 m) is old Monastery in the world and trek continue to Ghami approx 7 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 12: </strong>Trek Ghami to Samar (3620 m) approx 6 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 13:</strong> Trek Samar to Chhusang (2980 m) approx 2/3 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 14:</strong> Trek Chhusang to Muktinath (3800 m) via Gyu La Pass (4077 m) we can see the Panoramic view of Mt. Annapurna, Mt. Dhaulagiri and Tukuche Himalayan range trek continue to Muktinath approx 6 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 15: </strong>Trek Muktinath to Jomsom (2710 m) approx 4/5 hours O/N Lodge\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 16:</strong> Fly Jomsom to Pokhara (820m.) (Approx 25minis) transfers to hotel free day in Pokhara\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 17:</strong> Next day early in the morning drive to Sarangkot (1,592 m) to see Sunrise view and Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre and other many Peaks<strong>.</strong> Back to hotel and Pokhara City Sightseeing tour of Cave, Buddhist Monastery, World Peace Stupa and Temple\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 18:</strong> Drive to Kathmandu transfers to hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 19:</strong> Transfer to international airport for your final departure (Trip ends.)'),
(17961, 1042, '_trip_itinerary', 'field_58c80c7448611'),
(17962, 1042, 'cost_includes', 'Airport picks up and transfers to hotel\r\nFour night\'s hotel accommodation in Kathmandu with breakfast\r\nThree night\'s hotel accommodation in Pokhara with breakfast\r\nAccommodation in lodge /Tea house along the trekking route\r\nEnglish speaking local trekking guide\r\nNecessary porters to carry your baggage during the trekking (Two persons get one trekking\r\nporter)\r\nThree time meals during the trekking- Breakfast, Lunch &amp; Dinner\r\nAnnapurna Conservation Area entry permits\r\nTrekker’s Information Management system (TIMS)\r\nPrivate or local transport as per the program\r\nInsurance for Nepalese staff (Trekking guide and porters)\r\nTrekking Guide and porters\' salary, food, drinks, accommodations\r\nArrangement of Helicopter service for rescue in case of emergency in the mountain (the cost incurred during the rescue will be paid by your insurance company)\r\nMedical supplies (first aid kit will be available).\r\nGovernment Tax and office service charge\r\nAirport drop at the time of departure'),
(17963, 1042, '_cost_includes', 'field_58c80ca048613'),
(17964, 1042, 'cost_excludes', 'Lunch &amp; Dinner in Kathmandu and Pokhara\r\nNepal entry visa fee (you will easily get the visa upon your arrival at Tribhuwan International Airport)\r\nYour international flight ticket and airport departure tax\r\nPersonal equipments\r\nHigh risk medical insurance\r\nHot drinks, Alcoholic beverages, Telephone calls and laundry\r\nSoft drinks such as cola, mineral water\r\nBattery recharge, extra porters, shower etc during the trek\r\nEmergency rescue evacuation if needed (need to pay by your insurance)\r\nExtra night accommodation in Kathmandu and Pokhara because of early return from the trekking (due to any reason)\r\nTips &amp; Gratuities for trekking guide &amp; porter (s)'),
