(18366, 1047, 'trip_itinerary', '<strong>Day 01: </strong>Arrival and transfer to hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 02: </strong>Drive Kathmandu (1,350 m) to Chautara (1,419 m) by bus approx 3/4 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 03: </strong>Trek to Sano Okhrani (2,015 m) approx 5 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 04: </strong>Trek to Thulo Okhrani village (2,440 m) approx 4/5 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 05: </strong>Rest and acclimatization day in Thulo Okhrani village you will climb big forest to Nauling Danda (2,615 m) for the great mountains views and holy place at Nauling Danda then visit you will back to Thulo Okhrani village where you will have lots of great Monastery, Stupas (Chortens), Chereshi Statue, Kakani and oldest Mani wall walk around Thulo Okhrani village (2,440 m) overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 06: </strong>Trek to Baluwa (2,945 m) approx 5 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 07: </strong>Trek to Paga Bas (3,235 m) approx 6 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 08: </strong>Trek to Hille Bhanjyang (3,720 m) approx 5/6 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 09: </strong>Trek to Noshem Pati (3,615 m) approx 4/5 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 10:</strong> Rest day for Acclimatization\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 11: </strong>Trek to Panch Pokhari (4,079 m) approx 3/4 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 12: </strong>Trek to Panch Pokhari Ri (4,229 m) (Dopi Danda) &amp; back to Noshem Pati (3,615 m) approx 6/7 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 13: </strong>Trek to Doop Khang (2,145 m) approx 6/7 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 14: </strong>Trek to Mai kharka (1,765 m) approx 5 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 15: </strong>Trek to Gang Kharka (2,230 m) approx 5 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 16: </strong>Trek to Chamo Thang (2,684 m) approx 5 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 17:</strong> Trek to Tarkegyang (2,600 m) approx 5/6 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 18: </strong>Trek to Sermathang (2,590 m) approx 4 hours overnight at Camp\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 19: </strong>Trek to Melamchi Bazaar (870 m) and drive back to Kathmandu approx 4/5 hours\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 20:</strong> Free day in Kathmandu for rest and shopping\r\n<strong>Day 21:</strong> Transfer to international airport for your final departure (Trip ends.)'),
