(21300, 1092, 'trip_itinerary', '<strong>Day 01: Arrival at Kathmandu</strong>\r\n\r\nUpon arrival at Kathmandu International Airport, Meet <strong>High Mountain Himalaya</strong> airport representative for transfer service to hotel, rest of the day free for leisure. Overnight at hotel\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 02: Kathmandu - Nagarkot</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast in the hotel drive to Nagarkot, a beautiful hill resort abound in panoramic views of the surrounding Himalayas and Kathmandu Valley.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 03: Sunrise View from Nagarkot and back to Kathmandu</strong>\r\n\r\nWatch the sunrise over the mountains from Nagarkot and then drive to ancient town of Bhaktapur. Our professional guide brief you about the city\'s history and monuments, lunch in the gorgeous Durbar square. After lunch drive back to Kathmandu\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 04: Drive Kathmandu to Chitwan</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast in the hotel we drive overland to Chitwan National Park, check in the resort and begin the jungle walk inside the park. Overnight at resort\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 05: Full day Jungle Activities</strong>\r\n\r\nToday you will enjoy a full day wildlife activities such as: Elephant back safari, Nature walks, Canoe trip or boat ride, Jeep drive in the Deep forest, Elephant bathing, bird watching, Tharu Village tour etc. as per the program. Trained local a naturalist guide will escort you during the safari trip. Animals and birds you will encounter along the jungle trail are rhinoceros, crocodiles, bear, monkeys, several species of deer, pythons, peacocks, hornbills, woodpeckers (amongst more than 400 species of birds recorded in the park).\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 06: Drive Chitwan to Pokhara</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast drive to Pokhara (4-5 Hrs.) and transfer to hotel. In the evening boating in Phewa Lake. Overnight at hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 07: Pokhara Sightseeing</strong>\r\n\r\nPokhara is a place of remarkable natural beauty. The serenity of Phewa Lake and the magnificence of the fishtailed summit of Machhapuchhre (6,977 m) rising behind it create an ambience of peace and magic. Stretching from east to west, the Annapurna massif includes Annapurna 1 to IV and Annapurna South. The major sightseeing places in Pokhara are: Barahi Temple, Seti Gandaki, Devi\'s Fall, Mahendra Cave, The Old Bazaar, Museums\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 08: Drive Pokhara to Kathmandu</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast we drive back to Kathmandu. Rest of the day free for shopping and in the evening you will enjoy a traditional Nepalese dance program with us. Overnight at hotel\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 09: Enjoy Everest Mountain Flight</strong>\r\n\r\nTransfer to the domestic airport to catch Mountain Flight. You will fly over the \'Top of the World\' Mt. Everest and other Himalayan mountains. After 1hour flight you will be transferred to the hotel and have breakfast. In the day time you will be free for shopping or stay on your own.\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 10: Final Departure</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast transfer to international airport for your onward journey'),
