(22, 1, '2017-03-04 06:55:16', '2017-03-04 06:55:16', '<strong>Mountaineering in Nepal</strong> is one of the prime adventure activities. Nepal Himalaya stretches (800 km) from east to west encompassing the world\'s eight highest peaks that rise above (8,000 m) including <strong>Mt. Everest (8,848 m)</strong>. When Nepal opened its peaks to climbers in 1949, the Nepalese Himalaya has become a centre of attraction for mountaineering activity. Climbing Himalayas in Nepal has become a dream among the adventure enthusiasts and mountaineers in the world. Thousands of men and women come to Nepal for climbing various peaks and some of them become successful and some sacrifice their lives in the Himalaya.\r\n\r\nFully fledged mountaineering expedition is completely different from trekking and lower peak climbing in Nepal, as the expeditions include climbing above (7,000 m). In which snow is found almost throughout the year and require crampons ropes and other necessary climbing gears under the supervision and guidance of the climbing leader. We encourage the mountaineering beginners to attempt first easier <strong>trekking peaks</strong> such as Island Peak (Imja Tse), Mera Peak, Lobuje Peak (6,119 m), Pisang Peak, Chulu East Peak, Larkya Peak (6,010 m) and others below 6500m in altitude. Climbing lower peaks deliver as training courses for those attempting higher mountains above (8,000 m/26240 ft).\r\n\r\nThere are three seasons categorized for mountaineering in Nepal. The season begins from April to early June and it is the only season most of the expeditions carry on major peaks. The autumn and post monsoon season is considered the best time for mountain expeditions in Nepal. It is bitterly cold at high elevations from November to February, but due to the recent development of climbing equipment technology has allowed several expedition teams to accomplish what was thought before to be impossible for the winter ascent of a <strong>Himalayan peaks</strong>. Climbing to above (7,000 m) during the monsoon between June and August, is not practical from Nepal, though the north face of Everest (Tibet) can be climbed during August.\r\n\r\n<strong>Climbing expeditions</strong> to any other highest mountains in Nepal, in between (7,000 m) and (8,000 m) requires long-term planning and must be booked through locally-based government registered Trekking and Expedition Company. We have categorized mountaineering activity into three different parts – peaks above (8,000 m), below (8,000 m) and trekking peaks. <strong>(High Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expedition Pvt. Ltd. Bougha, Kathmandu, Nepal)</strong> Just write us an email <a href=\"mailto:sherpachangia@hotmsil.com\">sherpachangia@hotmsil.com</a> for any inquiry and cost and itinerary in details for mountaineering expedition in Nepal and Tibet.', 'Mountaineering Expedition', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'nepal-mountaineering-expedition', '', '', '2018-12-27 16:26:57', '2018-12-27 16:26:57', '', 0, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/?page_id=22', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(23, 1, '2017-03-04 06:55:16', '2017-03-04 06:55:16', 'Mountaineering page', 'Mountaineering', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-04 06:55:16', '2017-03-04 06:55:16', '', 22, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/2017/03/04/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(24, 1, '2017-03-04 06:55:47', '2017-03-04 06:55:47', 'Nepal is known in the world as a beautiful country of nature, culture, and adventure. The country is endowed with the high Himalayas, home to the world’s eight highest 8,000-meter peaks and cultural diversity. There is a lot more to experience in Nepal from the Himalaya, world- class rafting opportunities and the steamy flat lands of the Terai in the south.\r\n\r\nHere, you will find diverse ethnic people whose rich cultural heritage with festivals and rituals, songs and masked dances is unmatched by few places on this earth. You will explore many legendary temples and ancient monuments built in medieval times. Most of the Hindu and Buddhist shrines are intricately carved and adorned by statues devoted to the Hindu deities and Lord Buddha.\r\n\r\n<strong>High Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expeditions Pvt. Ltd.</strong> has designed a variety of popular tour packages which cover leisure tours, sightseeing tours, visit, Heritage tour, Pilgrimage tour, village tour and wildlife safari tour in national parks. You may combine adventure activities with cultural tours to make your holidays in Nepal more exciting and full of fun with extra cost. The adventure activities in Nepal could be white water river rafting, mountain flight to see Mt. Everest from close range, Peak climbing Paragliding, Bungee jump and so on.\r\n\r\nAll the tours in Nepal are organized privately from one-day sightseeing tour to a week- long escorted by our multi- language speaking professional and knowledgeable city tour guide in our private transport. Our city tour guide will escort you throughout the tour from the day of your arrival in Nepal till your departure to your home country. Our standard tour packages include 3-4 star level hotels and resorts including daily breakfasts, private transport, tour guides and heritage sites entrance fees. Whatever kind of expectation you hold, Nepal is always good at enkindling memories that last a lifetime. This peaceful Himalayan country is travelers\' paradise, a naturalists’ dream, and a living ethnographic museum.\r\n\r\nPlease look at our most popular Nepal tour packages and if you prefer to have a tailor-made tour itinerary of your interest and budget, one of our tour specialists can assist you to design the itinerary for you free of cost.', 'Nepal Tour', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'nepal-tour', '', '', '2019-01-03 11:22:42', '2019-01-03 11:22:42', '', 0, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/?page_id=24', 0, 'page', '', 0),
