(61, 1, '2017-03-15 16:25:08', '2017-03-15 16:25:08', 'Annapurna trekking is most popular trekking destination in Nepal. Everest trekking is known as Everest region trekking. Trekking in Everesrt region offers you great opportunity to have unique trekking experience while you are in Everest region trekking. Mt. Everest trekking area is located eastern part of Nepal and protected by the Sagarmatha National Park, established in 1976 with an area of 1148 square kilometers. Throughout In the Mount Everest trekking, trekkers are overwhelmed with views of unbelievable Himalayan views, Buddhist monasteries, and friendly Sherpa people . Mount Everest 8848m, the highest mountain in the world, which is known in Nepal as “Sagarmatha” the goddess mother of the world, has been the greatest attraction for nature lovers and trekkers equally. Mt. Everest treks take to you heart of the Khumbu Himalayan region include the Gokyo trekking , Everest base camp trekking trials mainly. Everest treks offer different spectacular trekking trail such as Everest base camp trekking, Kala pattar trekking, Gokyo Ri Trekking, Gokyo Cho la pass trekking, Renjo la pass trekking, Everest high pass trekking, Everest view trekking, Everest panorama trekking, Everest comfort trekking , Jiri Everest base camp trekking, Everest base camp trekking and Island peak climbing, Everest high pass trekking, Gokyo valley Tyangboche trekking, Everest view trekking, Gokyo Rejo la pass trekking, Mera peak climbing and Amphu lapcha pass trekking , Everest balcony trekking etc . Solu Khumbu Himalayan region is justifiably famous, not only for its proximity to the world’s highest mountain (8848 m.), but also for its Sherpa villages, wild animals and monasteries The primary goal of an Everest region trekking is the Everest base camp at an elevation of about 5463 meters. But you cannot see Mount Everest from the Everest base camp, so most trekkers climb Kala Pattar, an unassuming 5545m bump on the southern flank of Mt. Pumori (7145 m). From kala pattar you will see closed views of the Mt. Everest and other more mountains such as Mt. Lhotse , Mt. Nuptse , Mt. Amadablam , Mt. Pumori , Mt. Thamserku , Mt.Kantega, Kwangde peak, etc.\r\n\r\nSince Everest Trekking has been open Himalaya journey Treks and Expedition (R.P) has depth experience to operate different trekking destination in Everest region .Among above trekking destination in Everest region , Everest base camp trekking, Gokyo trekking, Gokyo cho la pass trekking, Gokyo Everest base camp trekking, Everest base camp and kala pattar trekking, Gokyo valley cho la pass Everest base camp trek is the one of the most popular trekking route in Khumbu Himalaya region. You will see spectacular Himalayan scenery, wild animals, Monasteries and Sherpa culture during your journeys in Khumbu Himalayan region. Even you have short period for the Nepal Himalaya trekking with less ambitious destinations such as Namche Bazaar, the administrative Headquarters of the Khumbu region; Khumjung or Thame, more typical Sherpa villages; or Tengboche Monastery. From Tengboche you will have an excellent view of Everest and its more spectacular neighbor Ama Dablam 6856m.To reach Everest region trekking trail you are able to arrange trip whether by bus from Jiri or by fly Kathmandu to Lukla. We Himalaya Journey Treks and Expedition – Nepal arrange all trekking destination in Everest region according to clients desire and holiday schedule. We arrange the Everest trekking tea house or camping /tented trekking in private or group join basis with family , friends, relatives , students/ academic trekking tour in large or small group size according to clients desire and holiday schedule with professional trekking guide who have been frequently in Everest region to present the lifetime experience!', 'Annapurna Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-15 16:25:08', '2017-03-15 16:25:08', '', 60, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/2017/03/15/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
