(121, 1, '2017-06-06 13:07:52', '2017-06-06 13:07:52', '<strong>Everest Two High Passes </strong><strong>Trekking</strong> is undoubtedly one of the most popular and adventurous trek comparatively to other normal trekking routes in the Everest region. You will cross over <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m)</strong> and explore the beautiful Gokyo valley and Gokyo Lake in the upper Khumbu valley. From the top of <strong>Gokyo RI (5,369 m)</strong> you will enjoy more distinct and closer view of the world\'s highest peak, Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), the 6th highest peak, Mt. Cho Oyu (8,201 m), Mt. Makalu (8,463 m) Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m) and many other snow-clad peaks of Everest region.\n\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass – Everest Base Camp Trekking</strong> after Gokyo Lake you will continue a long day trekking and cross over the <strong>Cho La Pass (5,420 m) </strong>and it takes about 9 hrs. Now you ascend slightly along the valley towards Cho La Pass. The Pass you can pass through is covered with rocks. While crossing the <strong>Cho La Pass </strong>is most of the time covered with blue Ice giving you a chill feeling. Here you can also, enjoy the stunning Panorama views of Lobuche Peak (6,119 m), Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Cholatse Peak (6,335 m) From Thagnag way crossing the<strong> Cho La Pass (5,420 m)</strong> the trail descends steeply down for an hour and then slightly descends all the way to Dzongla.\n\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass - Everest Trekking</strong> we follow the route Namche Bazaar- Thame Lungden, cross <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m),</strong> Gokyo Lake, Thagnag,<strong> Cho La Pass (5,420 m),</strong> Dzongla, Lobuche, Gorakshep, <strong>Everest Base Camp (5,364 m)</strong>, <strong>Kala Pattar (5,545 m),</strong> Dingboche, Tengboche, Namche Bazaar, Lukla and fly back to Kathmandu. While heading for Renjo La Pass and Gokyo valley you will spend one extra day at Namche Bazaar for acclimatization excursion around Khumjung village.\n\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass - Everest Trekking </strong>On the same day you will enjoy excursion around Sherpa’s villages, museum and many Buddhist Monastery and Stupas in Phakdingma, Namche Bazaar, Thame, Dingbocchce, Pangboche, Tengboche and Khumjung Buddhist monasteries Khumbu valley, and immerse in the beautiful sights of Himalayan Mountain range. At Khumjung village you will encounter the local people and experience their culture and tradition. Lots of renowned climbers of Nepal belong to Sherpa’s community from upper every Himalaya Valley. Visiting Khumjung Thame and Tengboche Monasteries makes your excursion more worthwhile.\n\n<strong>Everest Two High Passes </strong><strong>Trekking</strong> at the same time you will visit Tengboche where a famous Sherpa’s Buddhist Monastery is located. In Thame and Tengboche monasteries you will meet Buddhist monks and see their daily rituals. This is long trek with many cultural and natural highlights and recommendable only to those trekkers who are keen to walk at higher altitude for longer days.', 'Everest Two High Passes Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '52-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-06-06 13:07:52', '2017-06-06 13:07:52', '', 52, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/2017/03/17/52-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(122, 1, '2017-03-17 17:13:33', '2017-03-17 17:13:33', 'Lukla Everest base camp trekking is most popular trekking trail in Everest region. Lukla Everest base camp trek known as direct Everest base camp trekking . Everest base camp trekking offers a unique and unforgettable experience with awe inspiring views of the worlds highest and most beautiful mountains and grab the opportunity to visit the famed Everest Base Camp, from where Sir Edmund Hilary and Tensing Norgay made the first successful summit attempt of the phenomenal peak of Mt. Everest 29th May 1953. Mt. Everest Base Camp trekking continues to be one of the most rewarding adventure trip in Khumbu Himalaya range. Everest base camp trek offer eye catching Himalayan scenery including the Mt. Everest 8848m, Mt Lhotse 8516m, Mt. Nuptse 7855m, Mt. Pumori 7161m, Mt. Changaste 7550m, Mt. Lingterin 6679m, Mt. Amadablam 6856m, Mt. Thamserku 6723m, Mt. Kantega 6685m, Mt.Kusum Khagaru 6367m,Mt.Kongde 6011m,Mt. Khumbila 5761m(God of the Khumbu),Mt. Twache peak 6367m, Mt. Cholaste 6335m ,Island peak 6179m, Lobuche peak 6145m,Pokalde peak 5806m, Honku south peak 6119m, see different type of Animals such as musk dears, leopards, jackals, mountain Thar, birds such as Pheasant, long tails birds, relaxing with Sherpa culture. Autumn & spring season is best time trekking in Everest base camp but we Himalaya Journey Trekking arrange around the year as per trekkers wish and holiday frame.\r\n\r\nLukla Everest base camp trekking begin from Lukla after 35 minute flight from Kathmandu When land at that tiny airstrip in Lukla . Trekking in Everest base camp leads through the homelands of the Sherpa people, and will see Buddhist monasteries and close up views of Mt. Everest and neighboring Ama Dablam, Thamserku, Lhotse Nuptse , considered by many to be among the most beautiful mountains in Everest Himalaya region .After spent two nights at Namche Bazaar ,day for exploring and acclimatizing, which is an important factor in your enjoyment for the Everest base camp trekking , the bustling market town in the heart of Sherpa country. Himalaya Journey Treks & Expedition’s professional trekking guide led through Sherpa village , lush valley up to Goraksep the last teas house / lodge in Everest region then trail continue flat and ascend trekking in Everest base camp 5363m and next morning Kala pattar 5545m for superb Himalayan views of Mt. Everest and other mountains of Everest region. Then return trek from Everest base camp and kalapattar continues to delight adventurous souls with more spectacular mountain views, lush forested valleys, and opportunities to learn about the Nepalese religion ,culture and finally Lukla by flight back to Kathmandu.', 'Lukla Everest Base Camp Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '52-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-17 17:13:33', '2017-03-17 17:13:33', '', 52, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/2017/03/17/52-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(123, 1, '2017-03-17 17:16:29', '2017-03-17 17:16:29', '<strong>Everest Base Camp Trekking</strong> is one of the most adventurous and exciting treks that take you to the base of Mt. Everest - the world’s highest mountain. This trekking has been listed as “World’s Best Hikes out of 20 Dream Trails” by National Geographic.\r\n\r\nThe mountain scenery of the <strong>Everest region</strong> is incredibly beautiful. You will walk through multi-hued prayer flags, prayer wheels and intricately carved Mani stones dotted every hilltop and rock walls and trailside singing prayers to the gods with every breeze and every passing trekker’s. <strong>Trekking to Everest Base Camp,</strong> You can see prayer flags fluttering in the air either at the trail side or nearby Sherpa villages.\r\n\r\nWhile on the trek you will also experience Sherpa culture, their traditional lifestyle and hospitality. You will stop at numerous teahouses, sip a glass of sweetened tea with butter and salt or Chang (millet beer) and get a taste of hospitality of the Sherpa community. You will also visit Sherpa Museum at Namche Bazaar, Buddhist Monasteries and Stupas (Chortens) on the way and learn about how Lamaistic Buddhism influences Sherpa’s life.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Base Camp Trekking </strong>begins with an exciting flight to <strong>Lukla at 2,840 </strong>meters and then you walk through the picturesque Sherpa’s villages from <strong>Phakdingma (2,610 m) </strong>to<strong> Gorakshep (5,140 m) </strong>via<strong> Namche Bazaar, </strong>eventually culminating in the \"ascent\" of<strong> Kala Pattar (5,545 m).</strong> From Kala Pattar, the highest point of the trek, you will enjoy classic views of Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), Mt. Nuptse (7,861 m) Mt. Makalu (8,463 m), Mt Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Mt. Pumori 7,165 m), Mt. Kangtega (6,685 m), Mt. Thamserku (6,608 m), Cholatse Peak (6,335 m), and enjoy many other Peaks.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Base Camp Trekk </strong>most of the time you will walk above altitudes of (3,000) meters in the Khumbu and Imja valleys, whose skylines are dominated by the massive Peaks of the Eastern Himalayas. In April- May the Rhododendrons are seen in full blooming with orchids growing all along the trails in and around the <strong>Sagarmatha National Park.</strong>\r\n\r\nTrekking to Everest Base Camp does not require you to be an athlete or experienced hiker and climber. Anyone in good physical fitness and who exercises on a regular basis can comfortably and safely complete this trekking. However, you have to make difficult and sometimes long days walking to Base Camp and hiking up Kala Pattar but you have to make a slow and steady pace of walk.', 'Everest Base Camp Trekking', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'everest-base-camp-trekking', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:36:08', '2019-01-03 08:36:08', '', 49, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/?page_id=123', 0, 'page', '', 0),
