(180, 1, '2017-06-04 09:56:40', '2017-06-04 09:56:40', 'Lukla Everest base camp trekking is most popular trekking trail in Everest region. Lukla Everest base camp trek known as direct Everest base camp trekking . Everest base camp trekking offers a unique and unforgettable experience with awe inspiring views of the worlds highest and most beautiful mountains and grab the opportunity to visit the famed Everest Base Camp, from where Sir Edmund Hilary and Tensing Norgay made the first successful summit attempt of the phenomenal peak of Mt. Everest 29th May 1953. Mt. Everest Base Camp trekking continues to be one of the most rewarding adventure trip in Khumbu Himalaya range. Everest base camp trek offer eye catching Himalayan scenery including the Mt. Everest 8848m, Mt Lhotse 8516m, Mt. Nuptse 7855m, Mt. Pumori 7161m, Mt. Changaste 7550m, Mt. Lingterin 6679m, Mt. Amadablam 6856m, Mt. Thamserku 6723m, Mt. Kantega 6685m, Mt.Kusum Khagaru 6367m,Mt.Kongde 6011m,Mt. Khumbila 5761m(God of the Khumbu),Mt. Twache peak 6367m, Mt. Cholaste 6335m ,Island peak 6179m, Lobuche peak 6145m,Pokalde peak 5806m, Honku south peak 6119m, see different type of Animals such as musk dears, leopards, jackals, mountain Thar, birds such as Pheasant, long tails birds, relaxing with Sherpa culture. Autumn &amp; spring season is best time trekking in Everest base camp but we Himalaya Journey Trekking arrange around the year as per trekkers wish and holiday frame.\r\n\r\nLukla Everest base camp trekking begin from Lukla after 35 minute flight from Kathmandu When land at that tiny airstrip in Lukla . Trekking in Everest base camp leads through the homelands of the Sherpa people, and will see Buddhist monasteries and close up views of Mt. Everest and neighboring Ama Dablam, Thamserku, Lhotse Nuptse , considered by many to be among the most beautiful mountains in Everest Himalaya region .After spent two nights at Namche Bazaar ,day for exploring and acclimatizing, which is an important factor in your enjoyment for the Everest base camp trekking , the bustling market town in the heart of Sherpa country. Himalaya Journey Treks &amp; Expedition’s professional trekking guide led through Sherpa village , lush valley up to Goraksep the last teas house / lodge in Everest region then trail continue flat and ascend trekking in Everest base camp 5363m and next morning Kala pattar 5545m for superb Himalayan views of Mt. Everest and other mountains of Everest region. Then return trek from Everest base camp and kalapattar continues to delight adventurous souls with more spectacular mountain views, lush forested valleys, and opportunities to learn about the Nepalese religion ,culture and finally Lukla by flight back to Kathmandu.', 'Two High Passes Everest Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '52-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-04 09:56:40', '2017-06-04 09:56:40', '', 52, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/52-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(181, 1, '2017-06-04 10:05:23', '2017-06-04 10:05:23', '<strong>Everest Two High Passes </strong><strong>Trekking</strong> is undoubtedly one of the most popular and adventurous trek comparatively to other normal trekking routes in the Everest region. You will cross over <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m)</strong> and explore the beautiful Gokyo valley and Gokyo Lake in the upper Khumbu valley. From the top of <strong>Gokyo RI (5,369 m)</strong> you will enjoy more distinct and closer view of the world\'s highest peak, Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), the 6th highest peak, Mt. Cho Oyu (8,201 m), Mt. Makalu (8,463 m) Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m) and many other snow-clad peaks of Everest region.\r\n\r\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass – Everest Base Camp Trekking</strong> after Gokyo Lake you will continue a long day trekking and cross over the <strong>Cho La Pass (5,420 m) </strong>and it takes about 9 hrs. Now you ascend slightly along the valley towards Cho La Pass. The Pass you can pass through is covered with rocks. While crossing the <strong>Cho La Pass </strong>is most of the time covered with blue Ice giving you a chill feeling. Here you can also, enjoy the stunning Panorama views of Lobuche Peak (6,119 m), Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Cholatse Peak (6,335 m) From Thagnag way crossing the<strong> Cho La Pass (5,420 m)</strong> the trail descends steeply down for an hour and then slightly descends all the way to Dzongla.\r\n\r\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass - Everest Trekking</strong> we follow the route Namche Bazaar- Thame Lungden, cross <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m),</strong> Gokyo Lake, Thagnag,<strong> Cho La Pass (5,420 m),</strong> Dzongla, Lobuche, Gorakshep, <strong>Everest Base Camp (5,364 m)</strong>, <strong>Kala Pattar (5,545 m),</strong> Dingboche, Tengboche, Namche Bazaar, Lukla and fly back to Kathmandu. While heading for Renjo La Pass and Gokyo valley you will spend one extra day at Namche Bazaar for acclimatization excursion around Khumjung village.\r\n\r\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass - Everest Trekking </strong>On the same day you will enjoy excursion around Sherpa’s villages, museum and many Buddhist Monastery and Stupas in Phakdingma, Namche Bazaar, Thame, Dingbocchce, Pangboche, Tengboche and Khumjung Buddhist monasteries Khumbu valley, and immerse in the beautiful sights of Himalayan Mountain range. At Khumjung village you will encounter the local people and experience their culture and tradition. Lots of renowned climbers of Nepal belong to Sherpa’s community from upper every Himalaya Valley. Visiting Khumjung Thame and Tengboche Monasteries makes your excursion more worthwhile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Two High Passes </strong><strong>Trekking</strong> at the same time you will visit Tengboche where a famous Sherpa’s Buddhist Monastery is located. In Thame and Tengboche monasteries you will meet Buddhist monks and see their daily rituals. This is long trek with many cultural and natural highlights and recommendable only to those trekkers who are keen to walk at higher altitude for longer days.', 'Two High Passes Everest Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '52-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-04 10:05:23', '2017-06-04 10:05:23', '', 52, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/52-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
