(307, 1, '2017-06-04 12:33:52', '2017-06-04 12:33:52', '<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trekking</strong> is a classic 150-mile long trek that encircles the entire Annapurna massif and fills with stunning views of Annapurna Himalayan range consisting of Annapurna, Machhapuchhre, and Nilgiri, the Dhaulagiri Mountain Range and the Manaslu Mountain Range.\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna Trekking</strong> en route we pass through spectacular settlements inhabited by diverse ethnic group of people and landscapes from lowland farming country to alpine meadows to the Tibet-like country on the northern slopes of the Himalaya in Nepal.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The Trekking to Annapurna Circuit </strong>you will start in the foothills our trip at Besi Sahar (760 m) and reach after 6 days to the settlement of Manang village at (3,540 m) where you will rest one day for acclimatization and excursion for the Buddhists Monasteries and Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall in Manang and Upper Manang village also you will lots of enjoy the beautiful mountain views and Lake around the Manang Village.\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Round Trek </strong>in Manang village is no place anywhere in Nepal looks similar to Upper Mustangs’ landscape. The Round Annapurna Trekking is very interesting trips where you will lots of enjoys with mountains, rivers, waterfalls big forests of rhododendron, monasteries, Stupas (Chortens), Mani wall and also some time you can see the Animals like langurs, monkeys, tiger, pig, deer and many different birds etc. It lies behind the Annapurna range in rain shadow area which blocks the rain and is desert like landscape. From <strong>Manang</strong> we continue to ascend slowly and on day 10 of the trek we cross the famous <strong>Thorang La Pass, at 5,416 meter</strong>, and head for Muktinath, an important pilgrimage site for Buddhists.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trek</strong> crossing the <strong>Thorang La Pass 5,416 meter</strong> is where you will lots of enjoys walking on the snow and technically easy with wonderful experience. It is a moderate walk downhill to <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>, you will enjoys with stunning views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna mountain and Upper Mustang range. <strong>Annapurna Round Trekking</strong> after crossing <strong>Thorang La pass (5,416 m)</strong> we make easy but long descend into the Kali Gandaki River valley, with Annapurna and Dhaulagiri towering on either side. Then, we visit <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>. Where you can see and enjoys natural holy spring water 108 taps blessed by Guru Rinpoche’s (Guru Padma Sambhava), which have their source in or around Muktinath and bathing here is believed to bring good luck. Many people’s also collect the spring water in bottles to take home to relatives. Also at Muktinath is the legendary flame coming out of a rock natural fires, around which a Buddhists Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall. This place is very much sacred to visit both Buddhists and Hindu Pilgrims coming from different parts of Nepal, Tibet India, Bhutan and many others country.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trekking</strong> the further down we visit <strong>Tatopani </strong>where we take hot bath with by (Natural Hot Springs) really we lots of enjoys and relax you self. Then, we climb up <strong>Ghorepani</strong>, above <strong>Poon Hill (3,210 m)</strong>, to enjoy magnificent mountain views. where you will lots enjoys for sunrise view with other many mountains Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Niligiri North, Central, South, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Hiunchuli, Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre, Lamjuung Mimal and other many Peaks with green valley of Banthanti (2,300 m) and Pothana (1,900 m) back to Ghorepani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna Trekking</strong> and trek continue to Tadapani, Ghandruk village (2,030) and Naya Pul (1070m.) En route back to <strong>Pokhara</strong> we pass through many beautiful Gurung villages that populate this ancient trading route between Dhaulagiri and Annapurna mountain range.\r\n\r\nAccommodation and food is provided in the local lodges along the trail. Transport to<strong> Besi Sahar</strong> is by local or private coach depending on the travel plan and the return to Kathmandu from Pokhara is by road.', 'Annapurna Circuit Trekking', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'annapurna-circuit-trekking', '', '', '2019-01-01 12:16:29', '2019-01-01 12:16:29', '', 60, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/?page_id=307', 0, 'page', '', 0),
