 you will lots of enjoys walking on the snow and technically easy with wonderful experience. It is a moderate walk downhill to <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>, you will enjoys with stunning views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna mountain and Upper Mustang range. <strong>Annapurna Round Trekking</strong> after crossing <strong>Thorang La pass (5,416 m)</strong> we make easy but long descend into the Kali Gandaki River valley, with Annapurna and Dhaulagiri towering on either side. Then, we visit <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>. Where you can see and enjoys natural holy spring water 108 taps blessed by Guru Rinpoche’s (Guru Padma Sambhava), which have their source in or around Muktinath and bathing here is believed to bring good luck. Many people’s also collect the spring water in bottles to take home to relatives. Also at Muktinath is the legendary flame coming out of a rock natural fires, around which a Buddhists Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall. This place is very much sacred to visit both Buddhists and Hindu Pilgrims coming from different parts of Nepal, Tibet India, Bhutan and many others country.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trekking</strong> the further down we visit <strong>Tatopani </strong>where we take hot bath with by (Natural Hot Springs) really we lots of enjoys and relax you self. Then, we climb up <strong>Ghorepani</strong>, above <strong>Poon Hill (3,210 m)</strong>, to enjoy magnificent mountain views. where you will lots enjoys for sunrise view with other many mountains Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Niligiri North, Central, South, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Hiunchuli, Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre, Lamjuung Mimal and other many Peaks with green valley of Banthanti (2,300 m) and Pothana (1,900 m) back to Ghorepani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna Trekking</strong> and trek continue to Tadapani, Ghandruk village (2,030) and Naya Pul (1070m.) En route back to <strong>Pokhara</strong> we pass through many beautiful Gurung villages that populate this ancient trading route between Dhaulagiri and Annapurna mountain range.\r\n\r\nAccommodation and food is provided in the local lodges along the trail. Transport to<strong> Besi Sahar</strong> is by local or private coach depending on the travel plan and the return to Kathmandu from Pokhara is by road.', 'Annapurna Circuit Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '307-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-04 12:38:23', '2017-06-04 12:38:23', '', 307, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/307-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
