(379, 1, '2017-06-11 08:03:20', '2017-06-11 08:03:20', '<strong>Panch Pokhari </strong><strong>Camping </strong><strong>Trekking </strong>Panch Pokhari (literally means 5 sacred lakes) is surrounded by green hills at the base of Mountains like Jugal Himal (7,083 m), Pemthang Karpo Ri (6,865 m), Gokarpo Ri (6,889 m), Dorje Pahad (6,979 m), Bhairab Takura (6,799 m), Langpogang West (6,733 m), Gumba Chuli (6,226 m), Jugal Yang Ri (6,535 m), Phurbochyachu (6,637 m) and many other Mountains Peaks during the <strong>Panch Pokhari </strong><strong>Camping </strong><strong>Trekking </strong>trip. Also you will enjoy lots of many different big forests. You can see many Rhododendron and Pine trees etc. also beautiful Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens), big Amitabha Buddha Statue, Kakani (one kind of Stupa) and oldest Mani walls is stood nearby it and a couple of rest-houses are there for travelers. All these bluish colored high altitude lakes are sacred place of both Buddhist and Hindu.\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to Panch Pokhari</strong> offers pristine mountains views, rich culture and true adventure. This area lies north east of Kathmandu and can be organized the trip combining with cultural insights, unsurpassed beauty and biological diversity. We drive you from <strong>Kathmandu </strong><strong>(1,350 m)</strong><strong> to</strong> <strong>Chautara at </strong><strong>(1,419 m)</strong> experiencing beautiful mountains scenery through the terraced fields and rural villages belonging to different ethnic groups.\r\n\r\n<strong>Panch Pokhari </strong><strong>Camping </strong><strong>Trekking </strong>on the first day you begin the normal trails 2/3 hours, then narrow trails and steep paths. En route you will visit the villages inhabited by Sherpa and Tamang peoples. After two days you will arrive at the famous Sherpa’s<strong> village</strong> <strong>Thulo</strong><strong> Okhrani at (2,440 m)</strong> where you will have one day rest for acclimatization and excursions. Those day you will climb big forest to <strong>Nauling</strong><strong> Danda</strong><strong> (2,615 m)</strong> for the best mountain views and holy place at Nauling Danda then back to Thulo Okhrani village where you will lots of enjoy with beautiful Monastery, Stupas (Chortens), big Amitabha Buddha Statue, Kakani (one kind of Stupa) and oldest Mani wall in the District of Sindhupalchowk. These village of Sherpa’s are specially Buddhist. At village of Thulo Okhrani really you will get peace and relax there are many mixed trees with a big forest. Near the village you can see the wonderful mountains views around.\r\n\r\n<strong>Panch Pokhari Camping Trekking </strong>Your guide will give a short briefing on trekking, altitude sickness and the highlights of the trek which include the holy <strong>Panch Pokhari (Five Lakes) (4,079 m)</strong> here you will find peace and serene environment. Panch Pokhari (Five Lakes) is sacred for both Buddhist and Hindu, and every Year full moon day in the month of August many visitors throng to celebrate the Panch Pokhari (Five Lakes) festival. The Buddhists looking upon her mountains offers the viewers blessings for long life and freedom from accidents.  Lead a morning long <strong>Prayer</strong> <strong>(Puja)</strong> and this <strong>festival</strong> Hindu people change the <strong>Janai </strong>every year is held at Panch Pokhari (Five Lakes). Many <strong>Buddhists and Hindus pilgrimages</strong> pay a visit to this site. Panch Pokhari trek can be done all year round except in the monsoon.\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to Panch Pokhari Camping</strong> from Panch Pokhari (Five Lakes) Ri you will enjoy panoramic views of capital city of Kathmandu and many snow-clad mountains extended as far as Annapurna Himalayan Range the incredible <strong>Himalayan scenery</strong> and the life style of nomadic people unchanged by time. The unusual climatic and geographical terrain of the area offers a naturalist\'s dream for those who trek through this region. The top of Panch Pokhari (4,079 m) offers an excellent view of <strong>Jugal Himal Range</strong>, Rolwaling Range, Gosainkund, Langtang, Kanchenjunga and Makalu. You may also have chance to encounter Himalayan Deer, White Monkey, Musk Deer, Snow Leopard, Himalayan fox, Wild dog, Picas and civet cat along the route.\r\n\r\n<strong>High Mountain Himalaya Treks</strong> organize full board camping trek to Panch Pokhari (Five Lakes) supplying all camping equipments along with food, necessary porters and a well- trained cook.', 'Panch Pokhari Camping Trekking', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'panch-pokhari-camping-trekking', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:02:29', '2019-01-03 08:02:29', '', 376, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/?page_id=379', 0, 'page', '', 0);
