(466, 1, '2017-06-11 10:03:00', '2017-06-11 10:03:00', 'The arid and isolated <strong>Upper Mustang</strong> lies in the north-west region of Nepal. Trekking to Mustang inspires any travelers to explore centuries-old monasteries, barley fields created through the painstaking labour of local people, the high altitude trails and extreme deserts, religion, culture and life style of the local people\r\n\r\nThis trip gives you the opportunity to go where few have been before. Most of the trek keeps to arid, high deserts inhabited mostly by people of Tibetan stock. The men folk are either traders or farmers while the women mostly tend the fields.\r\n\r\nThe trek to this land of magic and mystery begins at Jomsom, following a flight to Jomsom and trek to Kagbeni, a ruined citadel town that guards the entrance into Mustang. Entering Mustang, we visit the 16th century monastery at Charang and the fortress city of Lo-Manthang. Here we observe the splendor and traditions of old Tibet. On our return from Mustang we may visit the sacred pilgrimage site of Muktinath and end our trek in Jomsom.', 'Upper Mustang Trekking', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'upper-mustang-lo-manthang-trekking', '', '', '2019-01-03 07:45:37', '2019-01-03 07:45:37', '', 666, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/?page_id=466', 0, 'page', '', 0),
