(484, 1, '2017-06-11 10:57:56', '2017-06-11 10:57:56', '<strong>Chisapani</strong>–<strong>Nagarkot</strong>-<strong>Dhulikhel Trekking</strong> If you are looking for a few days short and easy trek in the Himalayas, <strong>High Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expedition Pvt. Ltd.</strong> offers some of the most popular short hikes in Nepal. Some of them are in the Yolmo and Annapurna foot hills, and other is in the countryside starting from Kathmandu. While on trek you enjoy a close view of the Himalayan mountains range and have an opportunity to experience socio-cultural aspects of the areas.\n\nFor our well-designed short and easy treks, you need to be fit and passionate. No age bar limit. Even young kids to senior citizens can join the short treks.\n\n<strong>Trekking to Chisapani</strong>-<strong>Nagarkot</strong>-<strong>Dhulikhel </strong>is a shorter and less difficult one and very popular among the hikers who have limited time for holiday in Nepal. This trek is confined to the rim of the <strong>Kathmandu valley</strong> and the itinerary has been designed to explore the myriad wonders of nature, rural Nepal and view the awe inspiring Himalayan mountains range. The trip starts from <strong>Kathmandu</strong> <strong>(1,350 m)</strong> to <strong>Sundarijal (1,460 m)</strong> in a half an hour drive. A couple of hour’s uphill hike through <strong>Shivapuri National Park leads to Chisapani (2,165 m)</strong> via Mul Kharka (1,855 m) and Borlang Bhanjyang (2,430 m). This will be your first destination of the trek. Here, at Chisapani you will enjoy the real beauty of nature and spectacular panoramic Himalayan views being yourself aloof from the madding crowd of the urban areas. While trekking through Chisapani you will meet the local villagers and can have an opportunity to interact with them. Where you will lots of enjoys great panoramas.\n\n<strong>Short and Easy Trekking to</strong><strong> Chisapani</strong>-<strong>Nagarkot</strong>-<strong>Dhulikhel in Nepal </strong>Early in the morning you can see the best sunrise and many wonderful mountains views at Nagarkot will be the most fascinating and mesmerizing experience that you will ever feel. Dhulikhel is your last destination. Treading along the unexplored trails of Dhulikhel can be very exhilarating and enriching experience.\n\n<strong>Chisapani</strong>–<strong>Nagarkot</strong>-<strong>Dhulikhel Trekking</strong> <strong>Namo Buddha in Nepal </strong>you can visit Buddhist monastery, Stupas (Chortens) and shrines at (one of the most sacred site of Buddhist) where we will also learn about life style of the Tibetan Buddhist monks. On the way of Namo Buddha you can see many beautiful Himalaya Mountains ranges around. Those places are worth visiting as it will depict a holy feeling and tremendous peace in you. Your interaction with the Monastery, Stupas (Chortens) and local villagers experience their rich culture and tradition will be an extra charm of the entire trek.\n\n<strong>High Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expedition Pvt. Ltd.</strong> is committed to meet the aspirations of the trekkers by choosing the most romantic trekking route and entertaining them the best possible way.  We will provide the best guide to ensure that our clients will have the best experience of the trek ever imagined.', 'Short and Easy Trekking in Nepal', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '481-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-06-11 10:57:56', '2017-06-11 10:57:56', '', 481, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/481-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
