(500, 1, '2017-06-11 11:12:32', '2017-06-11 11:12:32', '<strong>Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel Trekking</strong> is an excellent trek for those who wish to avoid a long difficult trek or have time only for a short and easy one. Shivapuri, famous for watershed and wild life, is the second highest hill that surrounds the Kathmandu valley. This trek commences at <strong>Budhanilkantha</strong>. As you reach the top of the <strong>Shivapuri hill</strong> at (2,570 m) you can have the spectacular mountain view of Mt. Manaslu, Mt. Ganesh Himal Range, Mt. Langtang Range, Mt. Dorje Lakpa Mt. Shishapangma, Gaurishanker and many other peaks. From the hilltop you will also enjoy the sunrise and sunset view. In addition, <strong>Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel trek</strong> offers a good introduction to Nepalese rural life. The end point of the trek appears with two options either at <strong>Nagarkot</strong> or <strong>Dhulikhel</strong>.\r\n\r\nIf you choose Nagarkot option for exit, you will miss to visit typical <strong>Newari town</strong> with a temple-lined village square and cultural experience. In Nagarkot you will enjoy sunrise and panoramic views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna, Manaslu, Ganesh Himal and Lantang to the west. The village of Nagarkot is situated on the edge of the Kathmandu valley. It is just 32 km away from Kathmandu. On your way back from Nagarkot you may also visit Bhaktapur Durbar Square and many temples. If you go with Dhulikhel option for exit, you will enjoy a stunning panoramic view of several peaks from Langtang Lirung in the east, through Dorje Lakpa to the huge bulk of Gauri Shankar and nearby Melungtse (7181m) and as far as Numbur (5945m) in the east.\r\n\r\nDhulikhel town is situated on the main <strong>Arniko Highway</strong> towards the Tibet border. One can also go for short hike to <strong>Namo Buddha</strong> or take in many cultural sites around Dhulikhel.\r\n\r\nThis trek can be done throughout the year as each season adds beauty and majesty to this trek. The view point at Nagarkot offers memorable experience of the magic of mountains and offers superb views of the mountains as well as <strong>Kathmandu valley Nepal.</strong>', 'Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel Trekking', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'shivapuri-nagarkot-dhulikhel-trekking', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:24:12', '2019-01-03 08:24:12', '', 481, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/?page_id=500', 0, 'page', '', 0),
