ire region. Looking upon her mountain offers the viewers blessings for long life and freedom from accidents. On the full moon of Chaitra month (March/April) of every Year a big festival is held in her honor, to pay homage to her presence, in thanks of her protection and in hopes of success for the following year. Sherpa’s, Yolmo’s and other peoples from all over the region climb to the summit before the break of day in order to greet the rising sun. Local Lamas (Buddhist priests) lead a morning long prayer<strong> (Puja) </strong>and from the afternoon into the evening the local people lead the community in dance. Following local Sherpa’s and Yolmo tradition, Raksi, (corn, apple wine), Chang (barley beer) and traditional butter tea flow freely.\r\n\r\n<strong>Yolmo Trekking</strong> from the summit the whole ridge of the <strong>Ama Yang Ri</strong> <strong>Stupa (Chorten) </strong>is visible in both directions. To the south the Kathmandu Valley unfolds like a scroll. On clear day early in the morning the great Stupa (Chorten) of Boudha is visible, its great dome seemingly suspended above its surroundings..! The other side of Ama Yang Ri Stupa (Chorten) ridge (Dada) opens to the endless expanse of mountain with sky. Locals hold it as a very powerful place to meditate. On the other side of the hut is a low spiky bush with cactus (Throne) interwoven through its branches. Aside from grass it is the only vegetation on the otherwise barren mountainside.\r\n\r\n<strong>Yolmo Circuit Trekking</strong> Later on grand children of Meme Surya Sangay and their followers from Tarkeyghyang renovated <strong>Ama Yang Ri</strong> several times. Many pieces of the story are missing, but local histories and inherited memories only extend as far back as the early 1700\'s when villages first became established in the area. It is clearly mentioned that Ama Yang Ri Stupa (Chorten) and Chiri Gompa (Monastery) was first Gompa in the Helambu area and afterward Pema Choeling Gompa (present Tarkeghyang monastry) was built by Lamas.\r\n\r\nHistory mentions that <strong>Tarkeyghyang</strong> was established with eighty families with Meme Surya who was saint Lama and to get teaching from him surrounding Yolmo peoples. Lots of riches people migrated to <strong>Tarkeyghyang</strong>. That\'s how huge village in <strong>Yolmo Tarkeyghyang</strong> established which is also known as <strong>Langgyapsa</strong>.', 'Yolmo Cultural Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '350-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-11 11:44:57', '2017-06-11 11:44:57', '', 350, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/350-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
