(576, 1, '2017-06-24 16:19:11', '2017-06-24 16:19:11', '<strong>Yolmo Circuit Trekking</strong> is relatively a low altitude trek in Nepal, starting with a short drive from Kathmandu to <strong>Sundarijal</strong> and then trek to<strong> Chisapani</strong> (2,150 m) on along the <strong>Shivapuri ridge</strong>. You will walk below 3000m through temperate forests, green valleys and experience the Yolmo ethnic culture of high mountain area. Sweeping views of Mt. Langtang Lirung, Mt. Dorje Lakpa, Mt. Gaurishankar, Mt. Ganesh Himal, Mt. Pemthang Karpo Ri, Mt. Gurkarpo Ri, Mt. Dorje Pahad, Mt. Langpogang West and plenty of other peaks from Shivapuri ridge lures every nature and mountain lovers. The highest point of the trek is (3,690 m) at <strong>Tharepati La pass</strong> .The trail is snow-covered in winter and in spring rhododendron forests, a variety of wild flowers and distant horizons of snowy Peaks grace the trail, making you feel as if you are in Paradise. The entire <strong>Yolmo region</strong> is surprisingly pollution-free, peaceful, and captivating every village you can see the Buddhist Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens) and also Meditation Retreat center.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Yolmo Trekking</strong> Among the delightful villages in Yolmo region, <strong>Melamchi Gaon,</strong> <strong>Tarkeyghyang,</strong> <strong>Lhakhang Gompa</strong> and <strong>Sermathang </strong>are worth visiting as there are some very old Gompas (monasteries). Also, in Yolmo where you can see oldest Buddhist Monastery that name is Chiri Gompa. You can see the sunrise over the Himalayas from Sermathang and the also sunset, when seen from there is quite mesmerizing as well.\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to Yolmo \'Yang Ri Mountain\'</strong> is known fondly to the local villagers as <strong>Ama Yang Ri Stupa (Chorten) (3400 m)</strong>, means mother glory Peak. Ama Yang Ri Stupa (Chorten) is considered to be a dakini, who, by power of her compassion, has become a goddess protector of the entire region. Looking upon her mountain offers the viewers blessings for long life and freedom from accidents. On the full moon of Chaitra month (March/April) of every Year a big festival is held in her honor, to pay homage to her presence, in thanks of her protection and in hopes of success for the following year. Sherpa’s, Yolmo’s and other peoples from all over the region climb to the summit before the break of day in order to greet the rising sun. Local Lamas (Buddhist priests) lead a morning long prayer<strong> (Puja) </strong>and from the afternoon into the evening the local people lead the community in dance. Following local Sherpa’s and Yolmo tradition, Raksi, (corn, apple wine), Chang (barley beer) and traditional butter tea flow freely.\r\n\r\n<strong>Yolmo Trekking</strong> from the summit the whole ridge of the <strong>Ama Yang Ri</strong> <strong>Stupa (Chorten) </strong>is visible in both directions. To the south the Kathmandu Valley unfolds like a scroll. On clear day early in the morning the great Stupa (Chorten) of Boudha is visible, its great dome seemingly suspended above its surroundings..! The other side of Ama Yang Ri Stupa (Chorten) ridge (Dada) opens to the endless expanse of mountain with sky. Locals hold it as a very powerful place to meditate. On the other side of the hut is a low spiky bush with cactus (Throne) interwoven through its branches. Aside from grass it is the only vegetation on the otherwise barren mountainside.\r\n\r\n<strong>Yolmo Circuit Trekking</strong> Later on grand children of Meme Surya Sangay and their followers from Tarkeyghyang renovated <strong>Ama Yang Ri</strong> several times. Many pieces of the story are missing, but local histories and inherited memories only extend as far back as the early 1700\'s when villages first became established in the area. It is clearly mentioned that Ama Yang Ri Stupa (Chorten) and Chiri Gompa (Monastery) was first Gompa in the Helambu area and afterward Pema Choeling Gompa (present Tarkeghyang monastry) was built by Lamas.\r\n\r\nHistory mentions that <strong>Tarkeyghyang</strong> was established with eighty families with Meme Surya who was saint Lama and to get teaching from him surrounding Yolmo peoples. Lots of riches people migrated to <strong>Tarkeyghyang</strong>. That\'s how huge village in <strong>Yolmo Tarkeyghyang</strong> established which is also known as <strong>Langgyapsa</strong>.', 'Yolmo Cultural Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '350-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-24 16:19:11', '2017-06-24 16:19:11', '', 350, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/350-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
