(583, 1, '2017-06-24 16:36:56', '2017-06-24 16:36:56', '<strong>Ghorepani - Poon Hill Trekking </strong>is one of the shortest and most popular cultural treks to experience culture and lifestyle of the Gurung and Magar communities in the Annapurna region. The trail leads us through beautiful sub tropical valleys, dense forests of rhododendron and icy waterfalls. <strong>The Trekking to Ghorepani-Poon Hill </strong>we can lots of enjoys views around every corner during the trek soaring Himalayan peaks such as Mt. Dhaulagiri (8,167 m), Mt. Annapurna I (8,091 m), Mt. Machapurhre (Fish Tail) (6,993 m), Mt. Nilgiri (6,940 m), Mt. Hiunchuli (6,441 m), Mt. Annapurna South (7,219m), Mt. Lamjung Himal (6,931 m), Tukuche Peak (6,920 m), and some other many smaller peaks during the trip. From <strong>Poon Hill (3,210 m)</strong> we can see the best views of sunrise and Himalayan mountain range early in the morning. This entire trekking area is mainly dominated by the Gurungs and Magars both are ethnic people of Nepal. Dense Rhododendron forests, monkeys, tiger, deer, Jangle pigs, Jangle langurs, varieties of birds species, deep sub-tropical valleys, traditional villages, age-old tradition and culture, hospitable people, ever-smiling faces of the people, majestic mountain views with waterfalls are the major attractions of this trekking.\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to Ghandruk Village </strong>provides an insight into the lifestyles of Gurungs ethnic community of Nepal. Here, you will see how orderly rows of neat slate- roofed houses are clustered on the canyon wall amidst a complicated network of farming terraces. In addition, you will enjoy with great views of Himalayas renege that includes Mt. Macchapuchre (Fish Tail) and Annapurna South. From Pokhara it is just 42 kilometers drive and 5–6 hours in walking distance. <strong>Ghorepani-Poon Hill-Ghandruk Village Trekking</strong> is most interesting trekking place of the Annapurna region. Here in Jhinu Danda is one of the most popular places of the Annapurna region. Where you will lots of enjoys and takes with hot bath by (Natural Hot Spring) from the Jhinu Modi Khola (Jhinu Modi River). You will get fully enjoys and lots of great in your physically experience with exercise from this short trekking trip<strong>.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Ghorepani-Poon Hill Trekking </strong>Pothana (1,900 m) is another popular village where you will also encounter same Gurung ethnic community like in the Ghandruk village. This village is situated on the ridge of hill from where you can enjoy the spectacular view of Annapurna Himalayan range, Fishtail and green valley of Pokhara.\r\n\r\n<strong>High Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expedition Pvt. Ltd.</strong> can make the itinerary shorter without including Jhinu Danda as per client’s requirements. Those who have longer holiday can go via Ghandruk village, Jhinu Danda, Pothana, Dhampus, trek end in the Phedi (1,130 m) and Pokhara. And, those who have short holiday they prefer to trek only up to Ghorepani, Poon Hill, Ghadruk village and the trek end in Naya Pul (1,070 m) that is also possible. We recommend <strong>Ghorepani-Poon Hill-Ghandruk village trek</strong> because on this trekking route you will enjoy the best panoramic Mountains View, forests of Rhododendron, (Natural Hot Spring), experience Gurung culture, and lifestyle and make a circuit.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Ghorepani - Poon Hill Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '203-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-24 16:36:56', '2017-06-24 16:36:56', '', 203, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/203-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(584, 1, '2017-06-24 16:43:54', '2017-06-24 16:43:54', '<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trekking</strong> is a classic 150-mile long trek that encircles the entire Annapurna massif and fills with stunning views of Annapurna Himalayan range consisting of Annapurna, Machhapuchhre, and Nilgiri, the Dhaulagiri Mountain Range and the Manaslu Mountain Range.\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna Trekking</strong> en route we pass through spectacular settlements inhabited by diverse ethnic group of people and landscapes from lowland farming country to alpine meadows to the Tibet-like country on the northern slopes of the Himalaya in Nepal.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The Trekking to Annapurna Circuit </strong>you will start in the foothills our trip at Besi Sahar (760 m) and reach after 6 days to the settlement of Manang village at (3,540 m) where you will rest one day for acclimatization and excursion for the Buddhists Monasteries and Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall in Manang and Upper Manang village also you will lots of enjoy the beautiful mountain views and Lake around the Manang Village.\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Round Trek </strong>in Manang village is no place anywhere in Nepal looks similar to Upper Mustangs’ landscape. The Round Annapurna Trekking is very interesting trips where you will lots of enjoys with mountains, rivers, waterfalls big forests of rhododendron, monasteries, Stupas (Chortens), Mani wall and also some time you can see the Animals like langurs, monkeys, tiger, pig, deer and many different birds etc. It lies behind the Annapurna range in rain shadow area which blocks the rain and is desert like landscape. From <strong>Manang</strong> we continue to ascend slowly and on day 10 of the trek we cross the famous <strong>Thorang La Pass, at 5,416 meter</strong>, and head for Muktinath, an important pilgrimage site for Buddhists.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trek</strong> crossing the <strong>Thorang La Pass 5,416 meter</strong> is where you will lots of enjoys walking on the snow and technically easy with wonderful experience. It is a moderate walk downhill to <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>, you will enjoys with stunning views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna mountain and Upper Mustang range. <strong>Annapurna Round Trekking</strong> after crossing <strong>Thorang La pass (5,416 m)</strong> we make easy but long descend into the Kali Gandaki River valley, with Annapurna and Dhaulagiri towering on either side. Then, we visit <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>. Where you can see and enjoys natural holy spring water 108 taps blessed by Guru Rinpoche’s (Guru Padma Sambhava), which have their source in or around Muktinath and bathing here is believed to bring good luck. Many people’s also collect the spring water in bottles to take home to relatives. Also at Muktinath is the legendary flame coming out of a rock natural fires, around which a Buddhists Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall. This place is very much sacred to visit both Buddhists and Hindu Pilgrims coming from different parts of Nepal, Tibet India, Bhutan and many others country.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trekking</strong> the further down we visit <strong>Tatopani </strong>where we take hot bath with by (Natural Hot Springs) really we lots of enjoys and relax you self. Then, we climb up <strong>Ghorepani</strong>, above <strong>Poon Hill (3,210 m)</strong>, to enjoy magnificent mountain views. where you will lots enjoys for sunrise view with other many mountains Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Niligiri North, Central, South, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Hiunchuli, Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre, Lamjuung Mimal and other many Peaks with green valley of Banthanti (2,300 m) and Pothana (1,900 m) back to Ghorepani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna Trekking</strong> and trek continue to Tadapani, Ghandruk village (2,030) and Naya Pul (1070m.) En route back to <strong>Pokhara</strong> we pass through many beautiful Gurung villages that populate this ancient trading route between Dhaulagiri and Annapurna mountain range.\r\n\r\nAccommodation and food is provided in the local lodges along the trail. Transport to<strong> Besi Sahar</strong> is by local or private coach depending on the travel plan and the return to Kathmandu from Pokhara is by road.', 'Annapurna Circuit Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '307-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-06-24 16:43:54', '2017-06-24 16:43:54', '', 307, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayantreks/307-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
