(625, 1, '2018-02-11 03:54:52', '2018-02-11 03:54:52', 'Nepal is a small Himalayan country situated between China to the north, east and west part and India to the east, west, and south. It is very popular in the world for being home to 8 of the world\'s highest 14 mountains above 8000 meters including Mt. Everest, nine UNESCO declared World Heritage sites including Lumbini, is the place where Lord Buddha was born which is only 25 KM from his place Kapila Bastu. Namo Bouddha where, one of the previous life time of the Bouddha offer his own life to hungry mother tiger who recently had five cubs. Pharping is the place where Guru Padma sambhava did meditation for long time, subdued many nonhuman beings. You also can see naturally growing goddess Taras, miraculous hand print of Guru Padma Sambhava, many monasteries, Nunneries and retreat places etc.)\r\n\r\nIn this country, 28 million people live having over diverse 125 ethnic groups, 120 different ethnic languages, varied cultures, exotic traditions and festivals, unique art and architectures and above all very friendly people who always bestow the best hospitality to the visitors. The Nepalese people are renowned for their welcoming, friendly and hospitable nature. No matter where you’re from, you can be assured that you’ll be welcomed with a Namaste/Tashi Delek and a warm smile.\r\nIt is the richest country in the world due to amazing biodiversity: variable terrain, thick tropical forests to alpine vegetation teeming with a wealth of various flora &amp; fauna, thundering rivers, ice blue lakes, hidden valleys &amp; forested hills, all within a Nepal distance/measures about of 800 kilometers (497 mi) along its Himalayan axis by 150 to 250 kilometers (93 to 155 mi) across.\r\nThe erstwhile kingdom is almost trapezoidal in shape with a Nepal has an area of 147,181. The country is longer in length than in breadth, the narrowest point in the southern part merely 120 miles.\r\n\r\nThe scenery all over the country is breathtakingly beautiful with nice-looking villages, attractive traditional houses, captivating temples, lush meadows, forests, fast flowing rivers, deep canyons and the cold, barren regions at the base of the great Himalayas mountain peaks. There are also sub-tropical lowlands, dark, mysterious jungles abundant with diverse flora and fauna, and migratory and resident birds. The views also change with the seasons, thus providing the visitors with a kaleidoscope of brilliant phases of color like those of the different stages of the life cycle.', 'Nepal', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'nepal', '', '', '2018-12-20 17:24:34', '2018-12-20 17:24:34', '', 2, 'http://localhost:91/highhimalayatreks/?page_id=625', 0, 'page', '', 0),
