(789, 1, '2018-11-27 11:22:56', '2018-11-27 11:22:56', '<strong>Ganesh Himal</strong> is a remote area in the central Nepal bordered with Tibet. Very few trekkers have explored this area. This trek is named after one of the popular peaks-Ganesh Himal that lies between the Buri Gandaki river in the west , Bhote Koshi River in the east and Trishuli River in the lower section. The unique climatic condition, mixed vegetation and culture of the area makes trekking to Ganesh Himal region a wonderful experience.\r\n\r\nWe begin the journey to Ganesh Himal taking 9 hours long drive from <strong>Kathmandu to Syabru Besi</strong>. After spending overnight in Syabru Besi, the starting point for <strong>Langtang valley</strong> and <strong>Gosaikund trekking</strong>, we begin our trek toward <strong>Ganesh Himal region</strong> passing through newly opened trekking route named “<strong>Tamang Heritage</strong>”. There is also another alternative route to start trekking to Ganesh Himal via Dhading Besi .This is the shortest driving route which takes only 3 hours .We can choose either route to make entry into Ganesh Himal region.\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to Ganesh Himal</strong> area gives the trekkers an opportunity to observe the rich Nepalese cultural tradition from the closest quarters and intermingle with locals, hence giving the trekkers a sense of satisfaction. Besides it also offers an excellent habitat for a wide variety of rich flora and fauna at the foothills of the Ganesh Himal. Trekkers are impressed with display of berberis, primula, orchids and variety of ferns, the whole area sets a blaze by yellow blossoms of double Jasmine. The dense forest is teemed with Spanish oak, blue pine and in spring time blossoming of the rhododendron set whole forest alight in spectacular arrays of colors. Hot springs, Gorges and glaciers and magnificent sceneries are the highlights of <strong>Ganesh Himal trek.</strong>\r\n\r\nTrekking can be organized on full board basis with the support of our camping crew. The best time for Ganesh Himal trekking is from March to May and late September to December.', 'Ganesh Himal Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '402-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-27 11:22:56', '2018-11-27 11:22:56', '', 402, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/402-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(790, 1, '2018-11-27 11:24:53', '2018-11-27 11:24:53', '<strong>Tamang Heritage Trail</strong> is a newly promoted trek in the remote area of the Langtang region. The trail takes you through verdant midlands of Nepal experiencing the beauty of this mountainous region and the culture of the Tamang community who live here. The trail passes through traditional <strong>Tamang villages</strong> where life, culture, and crafts have remained unchanged since the beginning of the settlement. Warm traditional welcome hosted by the locals, their elaborate costumes, rich architecture of their mountain houses, and the ancient monasteries and places of pray add color to the experience of this trail. In addition to the cultural experience, the trek also offers wilderness experience through beautiful landscapes of alpine terrain, flat meadows, and rhododendron forests.\r\n\r\nThe trip to <strong>Tamang Heritage Trail</strong> begins with a scenic drive from Kathmandu to Syabu Besi (about 7-8 hrs), passing through Trisuli Bazaar on the way. At <strong>Syabu Besi</strong>, you spend the night at a lodge and start the trek early morning next day. It will be a relaxing walk through some truly breathtaking scenery which encompasses terraced paddy fields, charming villages, and serene valleys. If you trek in March-April, you will be amazed at the sight of rhododendron flowers in full bloom. The traditions of the region are pretty much similar to Tibetan culture; in fact, many of the inhabitants of this area have migrated from Kerung in Tibet and many have changed their surname and became Tamang. At <strong>Goljung</strong> and <strong>Gatlang </strong>villages you will observe Syabru and Mane local Tamang ethnic dances. In these villages you may also buy some exclusive handicraft items like traditional caps, mufflers and other items. At Tatopani you can enjoy hot bath in the natural hot-water spring. The ancient monasteries and houses adorned with rich wood engravings at <strong>Thuman</strong> is an unforgettable experience.Being off the beaten track, we offer you <strong>home stay</strong> facility with local family, basic accommodations and basic Nepali and Tibetan food.', 'Tamang Heritage Trail', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tamang-heritage-trail', '', '', '2019-01-03 10:45:58', '2019-01-03 10:45:58', '', 534, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/?page_id=790', 0, 'page', '', 0),
