(825, 1, '2018-11-27 12:19:05', '2018-11-27 12:19:05', '<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><b><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Lobuche East Peak</span></b><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\"> (6119m.) is one of the attractive trekking climbing peaks in Nepal. It lies in <b>Everest region</b> along with several other trekking peaks.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><b><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Climbing trip to Lobuche East peak</span></b><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\"> poses a challenge to both amateur and experienced climbers. However, it is not necessary that you have prior climbing experience. At least, outdoor experience and sound level of fitness is required.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Climbing trip to Lobuche Peak starts with an exhilarating <b>mountain flight to Lukla</b>. From Lukla you ascend slowly northward following the <b>Everest base camp trekking</b>route up to Gorakshep. En route we pass through Sagarmatha National Park , Namche Bazaar, Thame, Lungden, cross over Renjo La Pass, Gokyo, Thagnag, cross over Chola Pass, Dzongla, Lobuche, Gorakshep, Climb to Kala Pattar and further moves to Everest Base Camp. The base camp will be set up at 4,950m close to a lake in a rocky hollow at the base of the glaciated South-West Face. At base camp our experienced climbing guide will give you climbing clinic course and climbing technical skills so that you can build up enough confidence to achieve your goal to climb the summit.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">From Base Camp you will attempt to scale <b>Lobuche Peak high camp</b> at (5551m.) and set up camp at the base of the glaciated South-West Face. The views of Mt. Lhotse, Mt. Nuptse, Mt. Ama Dablam, Mt. Pumori, Mt.Tabuche and many other mountains from the high camp look surprisingly superb.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\"> The normal route for climbing to Lobuche East Peak is through South Ridge. The peak consists of several small summits and the true summit requires climbing steep snow and ice slopes to the top from the summit ridge. We have prepared Lobuche East Peak climbing itinerary in such a way which allows enough acclimatization and climbing preparation for the ascent of the Lobuche peak.</span></p>', 'Lobuche East Peak', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lobuche-east-peak', '', '', '2019-01-21 08:33:10', '2019-01-21 08:33:10', '', 20, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/?page_id=825', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(826, 1, '2018-11-27 12:19:05', '2018-11-27 12:19:05', 'Lobuche East Peak\r\n\r\nLobuche East Peak\r\n\r\nLobuche East Peak\r\n\r\nLobuche East Peak', 'Lobuche East Peak', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '825-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-27 12:19:05', '2018-11-27 12:19:05', '', 825, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/825-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(827, 1, '2018-11-27 12:19:27', '2018-11-27 12:19:27', '<strong>Mera peak</strong> is one of the highest trekking peaks in Nepal located south-east of Mount Everest. The trail for Mera peak climbing begins through the incredibly beautiful Hinku valley. This well-preserved and uninhabited Hinku valley below the Mera peak is one of the wildest and naturally most beautiful in Nepal having its massive moraines, glacial lakes and stunning mountain views.\r\nLike other climbing expedition to Everest region, we begin our trip to Mera peak with an exciting flight to Lukla airstrip. From Lukla we ascend gently to eastward, cross the Zatra La pass and reach the Mera La pass on the ninth day where we make our base camp for Mera Peak climbing preparation. Climbing Mera Peak is possible in a single day from the base camp but we avoid rush for safety reason. We allow proper rest and acclimatization and make use of high camp to ensure 100 % summit success.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDuring the climbing expedition  we ascend three summits of Mera  one after other .From the summit we will enjoy absolutely stunning and  panoramic view of 5 of the world’s 8000m peaks -  Mount Kanchanjunga, Mount Makalu, Mount  Lhotse, Mount Cho Oyu and Mount  Everest. This climbing trip can be organized both teahouse and full board camping basis with accommodation in twin sharing dormitory and food being served in a teahouse. One can just carry light day pack, rest is carried by yaks and our porters, and the average walking is 6 hours a day.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHigh Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expeditions offer highly experienced and professional climbing Sherpa and guides to ensure safe ascent and summit success along with the climbing permit and all other necessary logistics. This Mera Peak Climbing package trip can be flexibly adjusted to our clients’ requirements. Safety and comfort is our priority. For further inquiry and price, please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:sherpachangia@hotmail.com\">sherpachangia@hotmail.com</a>', 'Mera Peak Climbing ( Normal Route)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mera-peak-climbing-normal-route', '', '', '2019-01-13 13:55:20', '2019-01-13 13:55:20', '', 20, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/?page_id=827', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(828, 1, '2018-11-27 12:19:27', '2018-11-27 12:19:27', 'Mera Peak Climbing ( Normal Route)\r\n\r\nMera Peak Climbing ( Normal Route)\r\n\r\nMera Peak Climbing ( Normal Route)\r\n\r\nMera Peak Climbing ( Normal Route)', 'Mera Peak Climbing ( Normal Route)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '827-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-27 12:19:27', '2018-11-27 12:19:27', '', 827, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/827-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(829, 1, '2018-11-27 12:19:48', '2018-11-27 12:19:48', '<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; background: white;\"><b><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">The Mera Peak Climbing</span></b><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\"> via <b>Amphu Laptsa Pass trekking</b> is one of the most challenging adventure treks in Everest region. Situated in very sparsely uninhabited and unspoilt part of Hinku valley, Mera peak is considered one of the most popular \"Trekking Peaks\" in Nepal. Climbing Mera peak is meant to be an opportunity to all the adventure seekers who are physically fi and have a sense of adventure.From the <b>summit of Mera peak,</b>one will enjoy the amazing views of the 8000m high Himalayan Mountains range that includes Everest, Kanchenjunga, Makalu, Lhotse, Cho-Oyu and many other satellite peaks.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\"> With a spectacular mountain flight from Kathmandu, our trek will start by from Lukla. You will walk along a high rocky ridge past dense forests and cross several streams before reaching the high pass. After the high mountain pass you will finally reach the Hinku Valley. Trekking through this <b>Hinku Valley</b> you will sight blooming of rhododendrons in the spring season. Walking through the Himalayan pine forests is indeed a lifetime experience for every trekker. After several days of trekking you will cross over the most spectacular and difficult <b>Amphu Laptsa Pass</b> (5778m).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">After the Mera Peak (6654m.) summit, the trail will follow to the most spectacular and difficult Amphu Laptsa Pass (5778m). After crossing the pass you will continue walk down to Chhukung, Tengboche, Namche and down to Lukla. From Lukla you will fly back to Kathmandu next day.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Amphu Laptsa Pass trekking is a very high altitude trek through glaciated valleys and only strong, well equipped, groups can attempt this route. <b>High Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expedition</b> will provide unrivalled service, plenty of rope and anchors with full mountaineering equipment, hygienic food, reliable trekking crew and an experienced climbing guide to ensure that Mera Peak Climbing and Amphu Lapcha Pass trekking will be an excellent adventure experience in Nepal.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">After getting back to Kathmandu we will host a traditional Nepali dinner with ethnic cultural show.</span></p>', 'Mera Peak Climbing, via Amphu Laptsa Pass', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mera-peak-climbing-via-amphu-laptsa-pass', '', '', '2019-01-13 13:58:24', '2019-01-13 13:58:24', '', 20, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/?page_id=829', 0, 'page', '', 0),
