(833, 1, '2018-11-27 12:20:48', '2018-11-27 12:20:48', '<strong>Naya Kanga peak</strong> (5844m.), rises to the west of Ganja La Pass and the  south of Kyanjin Gompa (3,749m/12,297ft) is a popular but difficult peak to climb.It is located north from Kathmandu in the Langtang region. The normal trekking route that we follow to <strong>climb Naya Kanga peak</strong> is either Syabrubensi or Helambu region. The reward for climbing Naya Kanga is viewing of the spectacular mountains such as Langtang Lerung, (8,046m/27,749ft) Langshisa Ri (6,370m/20,894ft), Ganesh Himal, Pemthang Ri (6,836m/22,422ft), Pemthang Kapro Ri (6,830m/22,402ft) etc. The normal route of <strong>ascent to Naya Kanga</strong> is via the North - East Ridge over a line on ice and snow.Much of the climb is straightforward, but there is one fairly steep section where belaying is necessary.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe best way you can do is to <strong>cross over Ganjala pass</strong> (5130.m), the tricky but direct pass between Langtang and Helambu region. The climb to <strong>Naya Kanga</strong> is often combined with a crossing of the Ganjala pass and set up two camps .As there is no teahouse is available between <strong>Kyanjin Gompa</strong> and Ganjala pass we need to be well - equipped with camping gear, food and utensils and camping crew. The first camp is at Ganja La base camp some 500 meters above Kyanjin Gompa and the second camp is  a high camp at around 4,900 meters. The summit offers sublime views of the peaks lying along the<strong> Langtang Valley </strong>and into Tibet.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe route is approached on the trail across the Ganja La, the tricky but direct pass from Langtang to Helambu. The climb is often incorporated into a crossing of the pass and can be done with two camps. The first is <strong>Ganja La base camp</strong> some 500 meters above Kyanjin Gompa and the second a high camp at around 4,900 meters. The summit offers sublime views of the peaks lying along the Langtang Valley and into Tibet.', 'Naya Kanga (Ganjala Chuli)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'naya-kanga-ganjala-chuli', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:53:30', '2019-01-03 08:53:30', '', 20, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/?page_id=833', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(834, 1, '2018-11-27 12:20:48', '2018-11-27 12:20:48', 'Naya Kanga (Ganjala Chuli)\r\n\r\nNaya Kanga (Ganjala Chuli)\r\n\r\nNaya Kanga (Ganjala Chuli)\r\n\r\nNaya Kanga (Ganjala Chuli)', 'Naya Kanga (Ganjala Chuli)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '833-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-27 12:20:48', '2018-11-27 12:20:48', '', 833, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/833-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(835, 1, '2018-11-27 12:21:26', '2018-11-27 12:21:26', '<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Yala Peak (5732m) is one of Nepal\'s easier trekking peaks. Yala is a perfect peak accessible to a trekker without any climbing experience, who want to do trekking and peak climbing at the same time in Langtang region. From the summit of Yala peak the Langtang Himal as well as Shishapangma, just 20km from Yala Peak can be seen in a clear day.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">It takes 9hrs drive from Kathmandu to the trailhead at Syabhrubesi and then the trek begins through agricultural farmland, villages and forest of Rhododendron, conifer, bamboos, oaks and pines. During the spring the forest looks enchanting with flowers all around. The trail further follows the narrow gorge of Langtang River till it ends at the large alpine grass land of Kyanjin Gumba (3800m) where the glacier meets the meadow. You can see Yaks grazing in the meadow with the backdrops of snowy peaks of Langtang Ri, Langtang Lirung (7246m.), Dorjee Lakpa and many other unnamed mountains around you. This peak climbing trip enables you to explore the Langtang National Park, the home of Tibetan looking people-the Tamangs.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">After acclimatizing in Kyanjin Gumba and exploring the glacier, you hike to the Base Camp (4800m) located at the base of the Yala Peak summit. The summit climb requires only 700m of elevation gain consisting of non technical scramble with no objective danger. After trekking for 6 days you will have a solid acclimatization for safe climb to the elevation of 5500m.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">High Mountain Himalaya Treks offer full board package for Yala Peak climbing which includes climbing permit and all other necessary logistical support from arrival to departure. Upon your request we also customize our service up to base camp and the clients may arrange all required logistics from the base camp onward. However, our company arranges the peak permit, land transport and supporting staff.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Please contact us whether full board service or base camp service is required for Yala Peak Climbing. Our full board service includes airport pick up, transfer, accommodations, trekking and climbing route, hygienic high altitude food cooked freshly by our experienced cooks, experienced and professional trekking and climbing Sherpas and guides, departure transfers etc.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Yala Peak Climbing', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'yala-peak-climbing', '', '', '2019-01-03 09:16:46', '2019-01-03 09:16:46', '', 20, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/?page_id=835', 0, 'page', '', 0),
