(837, 1, '2018-11-27 12:21:43', '2018-11-27 12:21:43', '<strong>Chulu Far East Peak</strong> (6059m.) lies to north of the <strong>Manang region</strong> in a rain shadow enclosed by the main Annapurna Himal. Climbing to Chulu Far East Peak is not difficult like other trekking peaks. The summit of <strong>Chulu East</strong> provides the most breathtaking views of Mt. Annapurnas II, III and IV, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Glacier Dome, Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Tilicho Peak and Mt. Manaslu.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe start our trip from Kathmandu to Khudi via Beshisahar after a 6-7 hrs drive. The trail ascends gradually along the Marshyangdi river valley and eventually takes us to <strong>Pisang village</strong> where we leave the main trail and head toward the Chulu East base camp.On the trail you will encounter a wonderful variety of landscape and ethnic culture; from the subtropical lower reaches of the Marshyangdi valley with its terraced lands where Gurung ethnic group of people dominate, to rhododendron and pine forests.  Next day early morning we attempt summit Chulu Far East. From the base camp we follow the South-West Ridge on snow and ice up to the summit. After the summit we rejoin the main trail and descend Kali Gandaki valley crossing a high <strong>Thorung La pass</strong> at 5416 meter.Then we make descent to Muktinath, a sacred place both for Hindus and Buddhists located in <strong>Muktinath</strong> Valley at an altitude of 3,710 meters at the base of the Thorong La mountain pass.From Muktinath we walk to <strong>Jomsom</strong>, a beautiful town in the Lower Mustang located at an altitude of 2800m.\r\n\r\nMost of the climbing involves walking; including a high pass crossing.You will enjoy walking through interesting landscape with nice views mainly of the massif Nilgri. Snow-white spike of Dhaulagiri begins to peep out as you pass through.Your short day walk ends in a beautiful and clean village of Marpha. Here, you will find different architecture than anywhere else in Nepal. There are beautiful houses with white plasters and wooden balconies. The walk from Jomson to the center of <strong>Marpha</strong> can take even three hours in spite of the fact that it is just less than six kilometers in distance.\r\n\r\nYou can visit Buddhist Monastery and Stupa on the way to Marpha.From Marpha you can either take a drive or Mountain Bike to Tatopani where you can enjoy bath in natural hot spring.After Marpha your journey concludes in Pokhara. Any physically fit individual can do this Chulu Far East Peak climbing and trekking trip anytime in spring and autumn.', 'Chulu Far East Peak Climbing', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'chulu-far-east-peak-climbing', '', '', '2019-01-03 09:13:20', '2019-01-03 09:13:20', '', 20, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/?page_id=837', 0, 'page', '', 0),
