(907, 1, '2018-12-27 16:26:13', '2018-12-27 16:26:13', '<strong>Mountaineering in Nepal</strong> is one of the prime adventure activities. Nepal Himalaya stretches (800 km) from east to west encompassing the world\'s eight highest peaks that rise above (8,000 m) including <strong>Mt. Everest (8,848 m)</strong>. When Nepal opened its peaks to climbers in 1949, the Nepalese Himalaya has become a centre of attraction for mountaineering activity. Climbing Himalayas in Nepal has become a dream among the adventure enthusiasts and mountaineers in the world. Thousands of men and women come to Nepal for climbing various peaks and some of them become successful and some sacrifice their lives in the Himalaya.\r\n\r\nFully fledged mountaineering expedition is completely different from trekking and lower peak climbing in Nepal, as the expeditions include climbing above (7,000 m). In which snow is found almost throughout the year and require crampons ropes and other necessary climbing gears under the supervision and guidance of the climbing leader. We encourage the mountaineering beginners to attempt first easier <strong>trekking peaks</strong> such as Island Peak (Imja Tse), Mera Peak, Lobuje Peak (6,119 m), Pisang Peak, Chulu East Peak, Larkya Peak (6,010 m) and others below 6500m in altitude. Climbing lower peaks deliver as training courses for those attempting higher mountains above (8,000 m/26240 ft).\r\n\r\nThere are three seasons categorized for mountaineering in Nepal. The season begins from April to early June and it is the only season most of the expeditions carry on major peaks. The autumn and post monsoon season is considered the best time for mountain expeditions in Nepal. It is bitterly cold at high elevations from November to February, but due to the recent development of climbing equipment technology has allowed several expedition teams to accomplish what was thought before to be impossible for the winter ascent of a <strong>Himalayan peaks</strong>. Climbing to above (7,000 m) during the monsoon between June and August, is not practical from Nepal, though the north face of Everest (Tibet) can be climbed during August.\r\n\r\n<strong>Climbing expeditions</strong> to any other highest mountains in Nepal, in between (7,000 m) and (8,000 m) requires long-term planning and must be booked through locally-based government registered Trekking and Expedition Company. We have categorized mountaineering activity into three different parts – peaks above (8,000 m), below (8,000 m) and trekking peaks. <strong>(High Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expedition Pvt. Ltd. Bougha, Kathmandu, Nepal)</strong> Just write us an email <a href=\"mailto:sherpachangia@hotmsil.com\">sherpachangia@hotmsil.com</a> for any inquiry and cost and itinerary in details for mountaineering expedition in Nepal and Tibet.', 'Mountaineering Expedition', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-27 16:26:13', '2018-12-27 16:26:13', '', 22, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
