(926, 1, '2018-12-31 10:51:15', '2018-12-31 10:51:15', 'Everest trekking is most popular trekking destination in Nepal. Everest trekking is known as Everest region trekking. Trekking in Everesrt region offers you great opportunity to have unique trekking experience while you are in Everest region trekking. Mt. Everest trekking area is located eastern part of Nepal and protected by the Sagarmatha National Park, established in 1976 with an area of 1148 square kilometers. Throughout In the Mount Everest trekking, trekkers are overwhelmed with views of unbelievable Himalayan views, Buddhist monasteries, and friendly Sherpa people . Mount Everest 8848m, the highest mountain in the world, which is known in Nepal as \"Sagarmatha\" the goddess mother of the world, has been the greatest attraction for nature lovers and trekkers equally. Mt. Everest treks take to you heart of the Khumbu Himalayan region include the Gokyo trekking , Everest base camp trekking trials mainly. Everest treks offer different spectacular trekking trail such as Everest base camp trekking, Kala pattar trekking, Gokyo Ri Trekking, Gokyo Cho la pass trekking, Renjo la pass trekking, Everest high pass trekking, Everest view trekking, Everest panorama trekking, Everest comfort trekking , Jiri Everest base camp trekking, Everest base camp trekking and Island peak climbing, Everest high pass trekking, Gokyo valley Tyangboche trekking, Everest view trekking, Gokyo Rejo la pass trekking, Mera peak climbing and Amphu lapcha pass trekking , Everest balcony trekking etc . Solu Khumbu Himalayan region is justifiably famous, not only for its proximity to the world\'s highest mountain (8848 m.), but also for its Sherpa villages, wild animals and monasteries The primary goal of an Everest region trekking is the Everest base camp at an elevation of about 5463 meters. But you cannot see Mount Everest from the Everest base camp, so most trekkers climb Kala Pattar, an unassuming 5545m bump on the southern flank of Mt. Pumori (7145 m). From kala pattar you will see closed views of the Mt. Everest and other more mountains such as Mt. Lhotse , Mt. Nuptse , Mt. Amadablam , Mt. Pumori , Mt. Thamserku , Mt.Kantega, Kwangde peak, etc.\r\n\r\nSince Everest Trekking has been open Himalaya journey Treks and Expedition (R.P) has depth experience to operate different trekking destination in Everest region .Among above trekking destination in Everest region , Everest base camp trekking, Gokyo trekking, Gokyo cho la pass trekking, Gokyo Everest base camp trekking, Everest base camp and kala pattar trekking, Gokyo valley cho la pass Everest base camp trek is the one of the most popular trekking route in Khumbu Himalaya region. You will see spectacular Himalayan scenery, wild animals, Monasteries and Sherpa culture during your journeys in Khumbu Himalayan region. Even you have short period for the Nepal Himalaya trekking with less ambitious destinations such as Namche Bazaar, the administrative Headquarters of the Khumbu region; Khumjung or Thame, more typical Sherpa villages; or Tengboche Monastery. From Tengboche you will have an excellent view of Everest and its more spectacular neighbor Ama Dablam 6856m.To reach Everest region trekking trail you are able to arrange trip whether by bus from Jiri or by fly Kathmandu to Lukla. We Himalaya Journey Treks and Expedition - Nepal arrange all trekking destination in Everest region according to clients desire and holiday schedule. We arrange the Everest trekking tea house or camping /tented trekking in private or group join basis with family , friends, relatives , students/ academic trekking tour in large or small group size according to clients desire and holiday schedule with professional trekking guide who have been frequently in Everest region to present the lifetime experience!', 'Everest Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '49-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-31 10:51:15', '2018-12-31 10:51:15', '', 49, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/49-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(927, 1, '2018-12-31 10:54:32', '2018-12-31 10:54:32', '<strong>Everest Three High Passes Trekking</strong> is considered one of the most adventurous in the Everest region. <strong>Trekking to Everest three high passes</strong> begins with a 39 minute flight from Kathmandu to Lukla (2,840 m) the gateway to the Everest region. Then, we will begin our trek for 3 hrs to reach Phakdingma. Next day morning after breakfast we continue further uphill climb to Dudh Kosi valley and finally reach Namche bazaar, where we will spend two days for rest and acclimatization and excursion around Khumjung village.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Three High Passes Trekking</strong> on that day you will hike to Syangboche, one of the major spots you will enfoy for the view of Mt. Everest 8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Mt. Thamserku (6,608 m), Mt. Kangtega (6,685 m), Mt. Kusum Kangkaru (6,367 m) Cholatse Peak (6,335 m), Taboche Peak (6,367 m) Peak 38 and Kwangde Peak (6,168 m) etc. Then, you walk Everest view hotel and continue trek down to Khumjung village, a typical Sherpa’s village. Sherpa are ethnic people of mountain region. Lots of the renowned climbers belong to this community. In Khumjung you meet local people, see their lifestyle. Visiting Khumjung Monastery makes your walking more worthwhile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Three High Passes Trekking</strong> Next day, our continue trekking to Thame village where Sherpa’s are ethnic peoples of Mt. Everest region. Lots of the world renowned climbers such as <strong>Mr. </strong><strong>Tenzing Norgay Sherpa and Mr. Apa Sherpa</strong>  made his 21<sup>st</sup> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Everest\">Mt. Everest</a> summitted  and many other climbers belong to this ethnic community Mr. Tenzing Sherpa, the first climber to <strong>Mt. Everest</strong> <strong>(8,848 m)</strong> was born in this village. In Thame we will visit Thame Monastery and Stupas (Chorten) you will meet Buddhist monk’s in Monastery which is considered the popular Buddhist Monastery Everest region.\r\n\r\n<strong>Three High Passes Everest Trekking</strong> Everest high pass, there are three high passes in between namely, <strong>Renjo La Pass,</strong> <strong>Cho La Pass, </strong><strong>Everest Base Camp </strong>and<strong> Kongma La Pass.</strong> We cross all these three high passes one after another. This trek is considered to be one of the best journeys in the world, as we combine a strenuous trekking with extremely rewarding cultural and ecological exploration along the route. The newly explored <strong>Renjo La Pass</strong> <strong>(5,369 m)</strong> Pass located south of Gokyo valley and northwest of Namche Bazaar, <strong>Cho La Pass</strong> <strong>(5,420 m)</strong> situated west of <strong>Everest Base Camp (5,364 m)</strong> and north east of Gokyo and <strong>Kongma La Pass</strong> <strong>(5,535 m)</strong> south west of Everest base camp are all challenging and you must be well prepared to cross over them. After crossing over Cho La Pass you will reach the world\'s most sought- after trekking destination- Everest Base Camp and Kala Patthar (5,545 m). From the top of Kala Patthar and top of the Three High Passes you can see Mt. Everest and other mountain range.\r\n\r\n<strong>Three High Passes Everest Trekking</strong> can be attempted only those trekkers who have previous experience in trekking in high mountains and it could be challenging for beginners. If you are physically fit, then you can easily cross over all the passes and complete the entire trekking. <strong>High Mountain Himalaya Treks &amp; Expedition (P) LTD</strong> guarantees to make your wonderful lifetime trekking adventure in Nepal', 'Everest Three High Passes Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '185-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-31 10:54:32', '2018-12-31 10:54:32', '', 185, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/185-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
