(1007, 1, '2019-01-01 12:16:29', '2019-01-01 12:16:29', '<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trekking</strong> is a classic 150-mile long trek that encircles the entire Annapurna massif and fills with stunning views of Annapurna Himalayan range consisting of Annapurna, Machhapuchhre, and Nilgiri, the Dhaulagiri Mountain Range and the Manaslu Mountain Range.\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna Trekking</strong> en route we pass through spectacular settlements inhabited by diverse ethnic group of people and landscapes from lowland farming country to alpine meadows to the Tibet-like country on the northern slopes of the Himalaya in Nepal.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The Trekking to Annapurna Circuit </strong>you will start in the foothills our trip at Besi Sahar (760 m) and reach after 6 days to the settlement of Manang village at (3,540 m) where you will rest one day for acclimatization and excursion for the Buddhists Monasteries and Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall in Manang and Upper Manang village also you will lots of enjoy the beautiful mountain views and Lake around the Manang Village.\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Round Trek </strong>in Manang village is no place anywhere in Nepal looks similar to Upper Mustangs’ landscape. The Round Annapurna Trekking is very interesting trips where you will lots of enjoys with mountains, rivers, waterfalls big forests of rhododendron, monasteries, Stupas (Chortens), Mani wall and also some time you can see the Animals like langurs, monkeys, tiger, pig, deer and many different birds etc. It lies behind the Annapurna range in rain shadow area which blocks the rain and is desert like landscape. From <strong>Manang</strong> we continue to ascend slowly and on day 10 of the trek we cross the famous <strong>Thorang La Pass, at 5,416 meter</strong>, and head for Muktinath, an important pilgrimage site for Buddhists.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trek</strong> crossing the <strong>Thorang La Pass 5,416 meter</strong> is where you will lots of enjoys walking on the snow and technically easy with wonderful experience. It is a moderate walk downhill to <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>, you will enjoys with stunning views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna mountain and Upper Mustang range. <strong>Annapurna Round Trekking</strong> after crossing <strong>Thorang La pass (5,416 m)</strong> we make easy but long descend into the Kali Gandaki River valley, with Annapurna and Dhaulagiri towering on either side. Then, we visit <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>. Where you can see and enjoys natural holy spring water 108 taps blessed by Guru Rinpoche’s (Guru Padma Sambhava), which have their source in or around Muktinath and bathing here is believed to bring good luck. Many people’s also collect the spring water in bottles to take home to relatives. Also at Muktinath is the legendary flame coming out of a rock natural fires, around which a Buddhists Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall. This place is very much sacred to visit both Buddhists and Hindu Pilgrims coming from different parts of Nepal, Tibet India, Bhutan and many others country.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Circuit Trekking</strong> the further down we visit <strong>Tatopani </strong>where we take hot bath with by (Natural Hot Springs) really we lots of enjoys and relax you self. Then, we climb up <strong>Ghorepani</strong>, above <strong>Poon Hill (3,210 m)</strong>, to enjoy magnificent mountain views. where you will lots enjoys for sunrise view with other many mountains Mt. Dhaulagiri, Mt. Niligiri North, Central, South, Mt. Annapurna South Mt. Hiunchuli, Mt. Annapurna 1,11,1V, 111, Mt. Gangapurna, Mt. Machhapuchhre, Lamjuung Mimal and other many Peaks with green valley of Banthanti (2,300 m) and Pothana (1,900 m) back to Ghorepani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna Trekking</strong> and trek continue to Tadapani, Ghandruk village (2,030) and Naya Pul (1070m.) En route back to <strong>Pokhara</strong> we pass through many beautiful Gurung villages that populate this ancient trading route between Dhaulagiri and Annapurna mountain range.\r\n\r\nAccommodation and food is provided in the local lodges along the trail. Transport to<strong> Besi Sahar</strong> is by local or private coach depending on the travel plan and the return to Kathmandu from Pokhara is by road.', 'Annapurna Circuit Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '307-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-01 12:16:29', '2019-01-01 12:16:29', '', 307, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/307-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1008, 1, '2019-01-01 12:31:49', '2019-01-01 12:31:49', '<strong>Annapurna Circuit with Tilicho Lakeking</strong> is a classic trek that circumnavigates the huge Annapurna massif with an extension to <strong>Tilicho Lake Base Camp</strong>. The trail passes through a variety of different landscapes, from lush sub-tropical rainforest to alpine vegetation, from deep valleys and cultivated fields and high desert. The trek starts from village of Tal (1,700 m) and follows the River Marshyandi where you will enjoys with many through by beautiful River, forests and waterfalls on the way into before we reach Lower Pisang (3,200 m) in Upper Pisang you can enjoys with very nice mountain view and also you will visit beautiful Buddhists Monastery and Stupas (Chortens).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to Annapurna Circuit with Tilicho Lake</strong> where we will reach the highest with beautiful point of elevation - <em><strong>Mesokanto La Pas</strong></em><strong>s (5,099 m) and Thorong La Pass (5416 m)</strong>. En route you come across many different ethnic villages, have an opportunity meeting with the local people and enjoy spectacular views of massive Himalayan Peaks including the Mt. Annapurna’s and Mt. Manaslu. At Humde village (3,280 m) where you will lots of enjoys the wonderful Mountain View and Buddhists Monastery, Stupas (Chortens) and also you can see the Yaks, Cows, and Horses. And you are trek continue to Manang (3,540 m).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to round Annapurna with Tilicho Lake</strong> the Manang Village (3,540 m) is one of the most popular and beautiful places in Annapurna region. Where you will have a rest one day for acclimatization..! The rest day you will have a excursion for Buddhists Monasteries and Stupas (Chortens) Mani wall in Manang Village and Upper Manang village also you will a lots of enjoys with beautiful Lake and mountain views around the Manang Village (3,540 m) and we will walk to Lakeside near in Manang village (3,540 m)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna with Tilicho Lake Trekking</strong> from Manang we extend our Annapurna Circuit trekking trail further up to Tilicho Base Camp (4,150 m) where we will walk to above the trees line on the upper limits of the cultivations, in the north of the (Manang District) situated at the foot of <strong>Tilicho Lake (4920 m)</strong>. The Tilicho Lake is explored by only few trekkers groups. But this Tilicho Lake (4920 m) is very popular in Round Annapurna region. Where you will really enjoys with the beautiful Lake and then wonderful mountains views around the Tilicho Lake (4920 m). <strong>From Tilicho Lake you also have an option of crossing the challenging pass of <em>Mesokanto La Pas</em>s (5,099 m).</strong> That Crossing <strong>Mesokanto La Pass (5,099 m)</strong> is not so easy but that is possible to cross. Where you will lots of enjoys the views with two different Districts from top of the Pass.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Circuit with Tilicho Lake trekking</strong> after Tilicho Lake (4920 m) we will back to same way to the Khangsar village (3,700 m) From Letdar (4200 m) we continue to ascend slowly and on day 11 of the trek we will cross the famous <strong>Thorang La Pass, at 5,416 meter</strong>, is where you will lots of enjoys walking on the snow and technically easy with wonderful you will gets experience. It is a moderate walk downhill to <strong>Muktinath (3,800 m)</strong>, where you will visit an important pilgrimage site for Buddhists Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens), Mani wall and Temple.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Round Annapurna-Tilicho Lake<em>-Mesokanto La Pas</em>s (5,099 m) Trekking</strong> from Muktinath you walk onto Jomsom Bazaar. While descending to the west we enter the barren Tibet- like valley of Kali Gandaki which is considered the world\'s deepest gorge. At lower altitudes we walk through beautiful River with waterfalls, forests of schima and chestnut up to 2000 meter and beyond a great many species of oaks and rhododendrons especially in temperate zones at elevation up to 3000 meter. In this Annapurna region you will discover 30 species of rhododendrons along the trails.\r\n\r\nThe other highlights of this <strong>Annapurna Circuit with Tilicho Lake Trekking</strong> is that you can explore amazing ethnic cultures and different castes and tribes living at lower hills, mid hills and higher altitudes. The Kali Gandaki valley is inhabited by the Thakalis, in lower hills .On this trek you can experience both most Buddhists and some Hindu culture and religion. There are many Buddhist monasteries Stupas (Chortens) and Mani wall dotted on the high mountains.', 'Annapurna Circuit with Tilicho Lakeking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '300-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-01 12:31:49', '2019-01-01 12:31:49', '', 300, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/300-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1009, 1, '2019-01-01 14:11:47', '2019-01-01 14:11:47', '<strong>Annapurna Sanctuary Trekking</strong> is a picturesque walking journey that takes you to the foothills of the mountain Annapurna South. It is also popularly called <strong>Annapurna Base Camp Trekking.</strong> Trekking to Annapurna Sanctuary is highly recommended for those who love to explore the rich cultural diversities, typical Nepalese of Gurung and Magar villages, enjoy the flora and fauna and immerse in the panoramic view of mountain Annapurna, Dhaulagiri Himalayan range.\r\n\r\n<strong>The journey to the Annapurna Sanctuary</strong> kicks off from Pokhara with a one-hour drive to Naya Pul (1,070 m). From Naya Pul we trek to Tikhe Dhunga (1540 m) passing through terraced fields of potatoes, mustard, corn and vegetables, past small villages of stone-built houses.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Sanctuary Trekking</strong> also you will reach to<strong> Ghorepani (2,750 m)</strong>-<strong>Poon Hill (3,210 m) </strong>where you can see the best views around every corner during the trek soaring Himalayan peaks such as Mt. Dhaulagiri (8,167 m), Mt. Annapurna I (8,091 m), Mt. Machapurhre (Fish Tail) (6,993 m), Mt. Nilgiri (6,940 m), Mt. Hiunchuli (6,441 m), Mt. Annapurna South (7219 m), Mt. Lamjung Himal (6,931 m), Tukuche Peak (6,920 m), and some other many smaller peaks during the trip. From <strong>Poon Hill (3,210 m)</strong> we can see the best view of sunrise and Himalayan mountain range early in the morning. After<strong> Ghorepani (2,750 m), Poon Hill (3,210 m) </strong>our trek continue to Tadapani (2,590 m) via Deurali (2,990 m) and Banthanti (2,520 m) the trail leads us through beautiful sub tropical valleys, with many trees forests of rhododendron and icy waterfalls.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Base Camp Trekking</strong> while on trek we enjoy outstanding Himalayan Mountain views in the distance.  From <strong>Chhomrong (2,170 m)</strong>, where you will enjoy the views of Mt. Annapurna South (7219 m) and Mt. Hiunchuli (6,441 m) with very close and beautiful green forests. We walk down the Modi Khola (Modi River) gorge which takes us into the heart of the sanctuary and some of the most dramatic mountain scenery on the planet. Where you will have lots of enjoys with river crossing, waterfalls and then, higher altitude, through big forests of bamboo and of flowering mountains until you reach glaciated terrain. Also you can see in the mountains (Natural Honey Hunting). They hunt the honeys twice every season of (spring and autumn) in a year. The hives are in the rock approximately 200 to 400 meters from the ground by the indigenous Bees.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Annapurna Sanctuary Trekking</strong> walking slowly and steadily you walk through <strong>Machhapuchare base camp (3,700 m)</strong> and ultimately reach at <strong>Base Camp of Annapurna south (4,130 m)</strong>. The huge south face of Mt. Annapurna 1 (8,091 m) provides an impressive backdrop, while the up close views of towering peaks over 6,000 meter inspires a joy and lifetime experience for every trekker. With superb views of Mt. Machhapuchhre, Mt. Annapurna South and Hiunchuli in the backdrop, the base camp is a great place to spend one or two days.\r\n\r\nThe extraordinary variety of ecosystem is compressed into two weeks of <strong>Annapurna Base Camp walking.</strong> The Annapurna south facing slope of the base camp is covered with dense of tropical jungle of rhododendron and bamboo. On the other hand, the alpine region above 3,000 meter in the north offers dry rain shadow area with colder climate similar to the Tibetan plateau. Where in Jhinu Danda is one of the most popular places with by (Natural Hot Spring) off <strong>Annapurna Base Camp Trekking</strong>. Where you will lots of enjoys with takes hot bath by (Natural Hot Spring) in Jhinu-Modi Khola (Jhinu-Modi River).\r\n\r\nWe are return to Phedi via Landruk (1,565 m), Pothana (1,900 m), Dhampus (1,650 m) and catch our vehicle for Pokhara. This area is well developed with lodge facilities.', 'Annapurna Sanctuary Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '271-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-01 14:11:47', '2019-01-01 14:11:47', '', 271, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/271-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1010, 1, '2019-01-01 14:12:25', '2019-01-01 14:12:25', '<strong>Ghorepani - Poon Hill Trekking </strong>is one of the shortest and most popular cultural treks to experience culture and lifestyle of the Gurung and Magar communities in the Annapurna region. The trail leads us through beautiful sub tropical valleys, dense forests of rhododendron and icy waterfalls. <strong>The Trekking to Ghorepani-Poon Hill </strong>we can lots of enjoys views around every corner during the trek soaring Himalayan peaks such as Mt. Dhaulagiri (8,167 m), Mt. Annapurna I (8,091 m), Mt. Machapurhre (Fish Tail) (6,993 m), Mt. Nilgiri (6,940 m), Mt. Hiunchuli (6,441 m), Mt. Annapurna South (7,219m), Mt. Lamjung Himal (6,931 m), Tukuche Peak (6,920 m), and some other many smaller peaks during the trip. From <strong>Poon Hill (3,210 m)</strong> we can see the best views of sunrise and Himalayan mountain range early in the morning. This entire trekking area is mainly dominated by the Gurungs and Magars both are ethnic people of Nepal. Dense Rhododendron forests, monkeys, tiger, deer, Jangle pigs, Jangle langurs, varieties of birds species, deep sub-tropical valleys, traditional villages, age-old tradition and culture, hospitable people, ever-smiling faces of the people, majestic mountain views with waterfalls are the major attractions of this trekking.\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to Ghandruk Village </strong>provides an insight into the lifestyles of Gurungs ethnic community of Nepal. Here, you will see how orderly rows of neat slate- roofed houses are clustered on the canyon wall amidst a complicated network of farming terraces. In addition, you will enjoy with great views of Himalayas renege that includes Mt. Macchapuchre (Fish Tail) and Annapurna South. From Pokhara it is just 42 kilometers drive and 5–6 hours in walking distance. <strong>Ghorepani-Poon Hill-Ghandruk Village Trekking</strong> is most interesting trekking place of the Annapurna region. Here in Jhinu Danda is one of the most popular places of the Annapurna region. Where you will lots of enjoys and takes with hot bath by (Natural Hot Spring) from the Jhinu Modi Khola (Jhinu Modi River). You will get fully enjoys and lots of great in your physically experience with exercise from this short trekking trip<strong>.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Ghorepani-Poon Hill Trekking </strong>Pothana (1,900 m) is another popular village where you will also encounter same Gurung ethnic community like in the Ghandruk village. This village is situated on the ridge of hill from where you can enjoy the spectacular view of Annapurna Himalayan range, Fishtail and green valley of Pokhara.\r\n\r\n<strong>High Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expedition Pvt. Ltd.</strong> can make the itinerary shorter without including Jhinu Danda as per client’s requirements. Those who have longer holiday can go via Ghandruk village, Jhinu Danda, Pothana, Dhampus, trek end in the Phedi (1,130 m) and Pokhara. And, those who have short holiday they prefer to trek only up to Ghorepani, Poon Hill, Ghadruk village and the trek end in Naya Pul (1,070 m) that is also possible. We recommend <strong>Ghorepani-Poon Hill-Ghandruk village trek</strong> because on this trekking route you will enjoy the best panoramic Mountains View, forests of Rhododendron, (Natural Hot Spring), experience Gurung culture, and lifestyle and make a circuit.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Ghorepani - Poon Hill Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '203-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-01 14:12:25', '2019-01-01 14:12:25', '', 203, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/203-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1011, 1, '2019-01-01 14:17:53', '2019-01-01 14:17:53', '<strong>Langtang Valley Trekking</strong> lies just north of Kathmandu between the main Himalayan ranges and a slightly lower range of snowy peaks south of the Tibetan border. <strong>Trekking to Langtang valley</strong> takes us into high alpine yak pastures, glaciers and moraines around Kyanjing Gompa and offers us an opportunity to explore ethnic villages and diverse flora and fauna. <strong>In the Langtang valley </strong>you will find a small settlement of Sherpa peoples whereas the lower part of the valley such as Dhunche, Bharkhu and Syabru are mainly inhabited by Tamang ethnic group of people. Both these ethnic groups of people follow Buddhism and practice their respective culture and tradition. They earn their livelihood herding yak, sheep and producing buckwheat, potatoes, wheat and barley in the fields. Their houses are made of stones and wood covered with flat zinc roof that has tons of stone placed on top to secure them from flying.\r\n\r\nAccording to legend, the Langtang valley was discovered by one Buddhist monk following a runaway yaks. This is how the name-Langtang word is derived, Lang means Ox and tang means a field. <strong>Langtang Valley Trek</strong> can be completed in 9 days starts and ends in Kathmandu. We begin the trek from Dhunche heading uphill to Lama Hotel and Langtang Village until we arrive at the famous <strong>Kyanjin Gomp</strong>. Here, you will find Yaks everywhere. The view of Langtang Lirung and its glacier is beautiful. En route you will pass by the cheese factory and the ancient old monastery. From Kyanjing Gompa you can hike early in the morning up to <strong>Kyanjin Ri</strong> (4,773 m) and enjoy the view of the Mt. Langtang Lirung becoming golden and slowly turn to white.\r\n\r\nAfter exploring the <strong>Langtang valley</strong>, we retrace the same route to Syabrubesi from where we catch a transporter and drive back to Kathmandu.\r\n\r\n<strong>Langtang Valley Trekking</strong> is a highly recommended medium- hard trek that can be arranged throughout the year. <strong>High Mountain Himalaya Treks &amp; Expedition</strong> organizes all tours and treks all over Nepal according to the clients\' interest, time and budget.', 'Langtang Valley Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '336-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-01 14:17:53', '2019-01-01 14:17:53', '', 336, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/336-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1012, 1, '2019-01-01 17:01:05', '2019-01-01 17:01:05', '<strong>Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel Trekking</strong> is an excellent trek for those who wish to avoid a long difficult trek or have time only for a short and easy one. Shivapuri, famous for watershed and wild life, is the second highest hill that surrounds the Kathmandu valley. This trek commences at <strong>Budhanilkantha</strong>. As you reach the top of the <strong>Shivapuri hill</strong> at (2,570 m) you can have the spectacular mountain view of Mt. Manaslu, Mt. Ganesh Himal Range, Mt. Langtang Range, Mt. Dorje Lakpa Mt. Shishapangma, Gaurishanker and many other peaks. From the hilltop you will also enjoy the sunrise and sunset view. In addition, <strong>Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel trek</strong> offers a good introduction to Nepalese rural life. The end point of the trek appears with two options either at <strong>Nagarkot</strong> or <strong>Dhulikhel</strong>.\r\n\r\nIf you choose Nagarkot option for exit, you will miss to visit typical <strong>Newari town</strong> with a temple-lined village square and cultural experience. In Nagarkot you will enjoy sunrise and panoramic views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna, Manaslu, Ganesh Himal and Lantang to the west. The village of Nagarkot is situated on the edge of the Kathmandu valley. It is just 32 km away from Kathmandu. On your way back from Nagarkot you may also visit Bhaktapur Durbar Square and many temples. If you go with Dhulikhel option for exit, you will enjoy a stunning panoramic view of several peaks from Langtang Lirung in the east, through Dorje Lakpa to the huge bulk of Gauri Shankar and nearby Melungtse (7181m) and as far as Numbur (5945m) in the east.\r\n\r\nDhulikhel town is situated on the main <strong>Arniko Highway</strong> towards the Tibet border. One can also go for short hike to <strong>Namo Buddha</strong> or take in many cultural sites around Dhulikhel.\r\n\r\nThis trek can be done throughout the year as each season adds beauty and majesty to this trek. The view point at Nagarkot offers memorable experience of the magic of mountains and offers superb views of the mountains as well as <strong>Kathmandu valley Nepal.</strong>', 'Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '500-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-01 17:01:05', '2019-01-01 17:01:05', '', 500, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/500-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
