(1014, 1, '2019-01-01 17:02:18', '2019-01-01 17:02:18', '<strong>Namobuddha-Phulchowki Trekking in Nepal </strong>is begins with a short drive from Kathmandu to <strong>Dhulikhel</strong>, one of the picturesque hill resort town situated at 30 km away from Kathmandu. You will begin the trek to Namo Buddha and explore the surroundings. This trek is named after the <strong>Namo Buddha Stupas (Chortens)</strong>, one of the holiest sites for Buddhists in Nepal. In fact, there is beautiful Buddhist monastery around who founded by ven, Khenchen Thrangu Rinpoche and there are more than 250 monks living in the monastery. It says that one of his past Life <strong>Lord Buddha</strong> gave his life to a starving tigress and her cubs at this holy place.  We will keep one extra day at Namo Buddha for excursion around. That day you can also learn about Buddhist and life style of the monks.\r\n\r\nNext day from Namo Buddha you will continue walk up to <strong>Balthali,</strong> is a lovely village which sits on a plateau amidst terraced rice fields and thatched farm houses. During the hike between Namo Buddha and Balthali you will enjoy the view of the snowy Himalayan peaks. Overall, this is a relaxing area to hike and remains relatively uncrowned compared to other popular trekking routes in Nepal. Trekking to <strong>Namo Buddha and Phulchowki </strong>can be organized throughout the year except the rainy season (July and August).\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast you will trek further to Bebar Danda and ultimately enter into <strong>Phulchowki (2760 m)</strong> area is also one of the best viewpoints for viewing some of the highest peaks of the World including Mt. Everest. The highest altitude on this trek is Phulchowki at (2760 m) is the highest of the mountains encircling the Kathmandu valley and provides an ideal introduction to the birds of Nepal. Phulchowki\'s forests are also very rich in flora and butterflies. Mammals include Leopard, Yellow-throated Marten and Orange-bellied Squirrel. And you will continue gradual down hike<strong> to</strong> <strong>Godavari</strong>, spend a night there and next day you will have a short drive and return back to Kathmandu.', 'Namobuddha-Phulchowki Trekking in Nepal', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '508-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-01 17:02:18', '2019-01-01 17:02:18', '', 508, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/508-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
