(1064, 1, '2019-01-03 08:16:16', '2019-01-03 08:16:16', '<strong>Indigenous People\'s Trail Trekking</strong> is a newly developed culture-based trekking. The indigenous people\'s trail, the first of its kind in Nepal offers visitors unique and memorable exposure to one of the most culturally diverse areas of <strong>Ramechhap district</strong>. The trail is ringed by the Sun Koshi River to the south, the rapidly flowing Tama Koshi in the east and the Thulo Sailung hill in the north. The amazing sceneries and the breathtaking views along the trail offer a great experience to visitors.\r\n\r\nThe trail presents a natural blend of culture, language and ethnic diversity along with spectacular Himalayan panoramas, stretching from Number Peak and Kanchenjunga, the world\'s third highest peak the east, to Dhaulagiri and Annapurna in the west. Proper harmony and peace among the two major religious, Hinduism and Buddhism, can be observed where variety of gods and goddess, temples, stupas and monasteries are found in abundance. Out of the total population in Ramechhap district, 57.9% belong to indigenous communities comprising of Bramin, Chettri, Newar, Tamang, Thami, Sherpa and Yolmo. Majhis and Danuwar belong to fishing communities who live in riverine villages along the Sun Koshi and Tama Koshi Rivers.\r\n\r\nWe begin our journey to <strong>Indigenous People\'s Trekking Trail</strong> with a -7 hr drive from Kathmandu up to the trekking starting point at Dhunge via Mude. After the drive we begin our trek towards Thulo Sailung (3300 m), and follow the trail down to the Sherpa village of Khola Kharka where you will spend the night. Thulo Sailung offers magnificent views over Kalinchowk to the Annapurna, Langtang, Ganesh Himal, Rowaling, Everest and Kanchenjunga ranges, to the South the Mahabharata hills roll over the Sun Koshi River and down to the Terai below. During the festival of <strong>Saun Purnima</strong>, held on the full moon of July/August during which <strong>Tamang pilgrims</strong> crowd around the ruined Chortens at the highest point of Thulo Sailung. Nowadays, no blood sacrifices are permitted on <strong>Thulo Sailung</strong>. The shamans have surrendered to Buddhist Dominance and refrain from offering blood to the fierce female deities.\r\n\r\nFollow the trail The ‘Indigenous Peoples Trail’ is possible throughout the year, although the best season is October to December and March to April when the Rhododendrons are in bloom.', 'Indigenous People\'s Trail', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '796-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:16:16', '2019-01-03 08:16:16', '', 796, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/796-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1065, 1, '2019-01-03 08:21:13', '2019-01-03 08:21:13', '<strong>Rolwaling Valley Trekking</strong> bordering with Tibet is a beautiful <strong>Himalaya region</strong> located in the north-eastern part of Nepal. Trekking to Rolwaling valley can be a great option for adrenaline trekkers like traversing in the Everest and Annapurna region. It combines both uphill climbing experiences and crossing over one of the highest passes in the world, <strong>Tashi Lapcha Pass</strong><strong> (5,755 m)</strong> to enter the Khumbu (Everest) valley.\r\n\r\nYou will trek through several villages from lower elevation to higher elevation inhabited by people of varying ethnicity. Hindu people are mainly inhabited at the lower elevation with their own culture and tradition whereas the higher elevation specifically northern part is mainly home to the <strong>Sherpa community.</strong> In the remote villages you will have the opportunity to explore typical Nepalese culture as well as traditional lifestyle similar to Tibetan\r\n\r\nThe major challenges encountered during the trek are that you will traverse over entire snow paths for a few days during post-monsoon season, need to cross dense alpine forests and gradually attain uphill elevation. One of the highlight of the trek is that you will visit <em><strong>Bigu Gompa</strong></em><em> (Nunnery)</em> <em>and interact with the Buddhist nuns</em>. You will also enjoy the close sightings of few of the world\'s highest mountains en route- <strong>Everest, Lhotse, Makalu</strong> and many other peaks. The most popular Himalayan peaks of the <strong>Rolwaling region</strong> are Melungtse (7,181 m) and Melungtse II (7,023 m) and Gauri Shankar (7,134 m) and around 50 minor peaks.\r\n\r\nTea house facility is still not available all over the Rolwaling region except a few places. This is why we have to organize trekking on full board camping basis. As Rolwaling valley lies in one of the most remote and wild areas, trekkers should be in good health and physical condition with previous walking experience to attempt <strong>Rolwaling valley trekking</strong>. If you need more information or interested to trek in this region fell free to contact us.', 'Rolwaling Valley Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '798-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:21:13', '2019-01-03 08:21:13', '', 798, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/798-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1066, 1, '2019-01-03 08:24:12', '2019-01-03 08:24:12', '<strong>Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel Trekking</strong> is an excellent trek for those who wish to avoid a long difficult trek or have time only for a short and easy one. Shivapuri, famous for watershed and wild life, is the second highest hill that surrounds the Kathmandu valley. This trek commences at <strong>Budhanilkantha</strong>. As you reach the top of the <strong>Shivapuri hill</strong> at (2,570 m) you can have the spectacular mountain view of Mt. Manaslu, Mt. Ganesh Himal Range, Mt. Langtang Range, Mt. Dorje Lakpa Mt. Shishapangma, Gaurishanker and many other peaks. From the hilltop you will also enjoy the sunrise and sunset view. In addition, <strong>Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel trek</strong> offers a good introduction to Nepalese rural life. The end point of the trek appears with two options either at <strong>Nagarkot</strong> or <strong>Dhulikhel</strong>.\r\n\r\nIf you choose Nagarkot option for exit, you will miss to visit typical <strong>Newari town</strong> with a temple-lined village square and cultural experience. In Nagarkot you will enjoy sunrise and panoramic views of Dhaulagiri, Annapurna, Manaslu, Ganesh Himal and Lantang to the west. The village of Nagarkot is situated on the edge of the Kathmandu valley. It is just 32 km away from Kathmandu. On your way back from Nagarkot you may also visit Bhaktapur Durbar Square and many temples. If you go with Dhulikhel option for exit, you will enjoy a stunning panoramic view of several peaks from Langtang Lirung in the east, through Dorje Lakpa to the huge bulk of Gauri Shankar and nearby Melungtse (7181m) and as far as Numbur (5945m) in the east.\r\n\r\nDhulikhel town is situated on the main <strong>Arniko Highway</strong> towards the Tibet border. One can also go for short hike to <strong>Namo Buddha</strong> or take in many cultural sites around Dhulikhel.\r\n\r\nThis trek can be done throughout the year as each season adds beauty and majesty to this trek. The view point at Nagarkot offers memorable experience of the magic of mountains and offers superb views of the mountains as well as <strong>Kathmandu valley Nepal.</strong>', 'Shivapuri-Nagarkot-Dhulikhel Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '500-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:24:12', '2019-01-03 08:24:12', '', 500, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/500-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1067, 1, '2019-01-03 08:25:05', '2019-01-03 08:25:05', '<strong>Namobuddha-Phulchowki Trekking in Nepal </strong>is begins with a short drive from Kathmandu to <strong>Dhulikhel</strong>, one of the picturesque hill resort town situated at 30 km away from Kathmandu. You will begin the trek to Namo Buddha and explore the surroundings. This trek is named after the <strong>Namo Buddha Stupas (Chortens)</strong>, one of the holiest sites for Buddhists in Nepal. In fact, there is beautiful Buddhist monastery around who founded by ven, Khenchen Thrangu Rinpoche and there are more than 250 monks living in the monastery. It says that one of his past Life <strong>Lord Buddha</strong> gave his life to a starving tigress and her cubs at this holy place.  We will keep one extra day at Namo Buddha for excursion around. That day you can also learn about Buddhist and life style of the monks.\r\n\r\nNext day from Namo Buddha you will continue walk up to <strong>Balthali,</strong> is a lovely village which sits on a plateau amidst terraced rice fields and thatched farm houses. During the hike between Namo Buddha and Balthali you will enjoy the view of the snowy Himalayan peaks. Overall, this is a relaxing area to hike and remains relatively uncrowned compared to other popular trekking routes in Nepal. Trekking to <strong>Namo Buddha and Phulchowki </strong>can be organized throughout the year except the rainy season (July and August).\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast you will trek further to Bebar Danda and ultimately enter into <strong>Phulchowki (2760 m)</strong> area is also one of the best viewpoints for viewing some of the highest peaks of the World including Mt. Everest. The highest altitude on this trek is Phulchowki at (2760 m) is the highest of the mountains encircling the Kathmandu valley and provides an ideal introduction to the birds of Nepal. Phulchowki\'s forests are also very rich in flora and butterflies. Mammals include Leopard, Yellow-throated Marten and Orange-bellied Squirrel. And you will continue gradual down hike<strong> to</strong> <strong>Godavari</strong>, spend a night there and next day you will have a short drive and return back to Kathmandu.', 'Namobuddha-Phulchowki Trekking in Nepal', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '508-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:25:05', '2019-01-03 08:25:05', '', 508, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/508-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1068, 1, '2019-01-03 08:25:58', '2019-01-03 08:25:58', '<strong>Cultural Trekking to Annapurna Region.......!</strong>\r\n\r\nThis is a short and easy trek in to the <strong>Annapurna region</strong> designed for trekkers with a limited time schedule. <strong>Cultural Trek to Annapurna Region</strong> offers some wonderful close- up views of the <strong>Himalayan mountain</strong> range. The trip starts at Phedi after 2 hours drive from Pokhara.\r\n\r\nAfter Phedi you will begin the trek through patchwork valleys, dense mossy forests and past waterfalls where you can stop to cool yourself. Around every corner you will be tempted by a tantalizing glimpse of the high mountains, whole horizons will be revealed to you as you slowly ascend the higher elevations. During the hill walk, you pass through different Gurung, Magar and Brahmin villages where you get an insight into their diverse cultural and social practices. In a short period, you can experience their colorful culture of the local people and find how Buddhist and Hindu people are living in harmony and peace.\r\n\r\nAll the way you follow the <strong>Modi gorge valley</strong> through rhododendron and orchid forest and reach a culturally rich village called Pothana where <strong>Gurung ethnic community</strong> is inhabited in majority. During the trek you can see the panoramic views of Mt. Machapuchhre (fishtail), Annapurna South, Lamjung Himal, Hiunchuli (6441m) and Dhaulagiri more distinctly if weather permits. An excursion around the village you will have an opportunity to watch the daily activities of the villagers from milching the buffalows to their daily chores on the farms.After <strong>Pothana village</strong> you will walk further uphill to another village called <strong>Ghandruk village in Nepal</strong> where you will find the same Gurung ethnic community who are known is \'<strong>Gurkhas</strong>\'. They have a glorious history created in the <strong>Second World War</strong>. Here, you will see how the traditional houses with stone roofs have been preserved till today and during your stay in the village you can visit the local museum.', 'Cultural Trekking to Annapurna Region', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '515-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:25:58', '2019-01-03 08:25:58', '', 515, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/515-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1069, 1, '2019-01-03 10:51:39', '2019-01-03 10:51:39', '<strong>Helambu Circuit</strong> is relatively a low altitude trek in Nepal, starting with a short drive from Kathmandu to <strong>Sundarijal</strong> and then trek to<strong> Chisapani</strong> (2150 m) on along the <strong>Shivapuri ridge</strong>. You walk below 3000m through temperate forests, green valleys and experience the Yalmo ethnic culture of high mountain area. Sweeping views of Langtang Lirung, Dorje Lakpa, Gaurishankar, Ganesa Himal, Yala Peak and plenty of other peaks from Shivapuri ridge lures every nature and mountain lovers. The highest point of the trek is 3600m at <strong>Tharepati La pass</strong> .The trail is snow-covered in winter and in spring rhododendron forests, a variety of wild flowers and distant horizons of snowy Peaks grace the trail, making you feel as if you are in Paradise. The entire <strong>Helambu region</strong> is surprisingly pollution-free, peaceful and captivating.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAmong the delightful villages in Helambu region, <strong>Tarke Gyang</strong> and <strong>Sermathang </strong>are worth visiting as there are some very old Gompas (monasteries). You can also see the sunrise over the Himalayas from Sermathang and the sunset, when seen from there, is quite mesmerizing as well.\n\n<strong>\'Yang Rill Mountain\'</strong> is known fondly to the local villagers as <strong>Ama Yangri</strong>, meaning mother <strong>Yangri</strong>. Ama Yangri is considered to be a dakini, who, by power of her compassion, has become a goddess protector of the entire region. Looking upon her mountain offers the viewers blessings for long life and freedom from accidents. On the full moon of Chaitra (March - April) a big festival is held in her honor, to pay homage to her presence, in thanks of her protection and in hopes of success for the following year. Sherpa (Hyolmo) peoples from all over the region climb to the summit before the break of day in order to greet the rising sun. Local Lamas (Buddhist priests) lead a morning long Puja and from the afternoon into the evening the local people lead the community in dance. Following local Sherpa (Hyolmo) tradition, Raksi (corn, apple wine) ,Chang (barley beer) and traditional butter tea flow freely.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFrom the summit the whole ridge of the <strong>Yangri</strong> is visible in both directions. To the south the Kathmandu Valley unfolds like a scroll. On clear day and in the early morning the Great Stupa of Boudha is visible, its great dome seemingly suspended above its surroundings! The other side of angri ridge (Danda) opens to the endless expanse of mountain and sky. Locals hold it as a very powerful place to meditate. On the other side of the hut is a low spiky bush with katas (Throne) interwoven through its branches. Aside from grass it is the only vegetation on the otherwise barren mountainside.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nLater on grand grand children of Meme Surya Senge-ge and their followers from Tarkeyghyang renovated <strong>Ama Yangri</strong> several times. Many pieces of the story are missing, but local histories and inherited memories only extend as far back as the early 1700\'s when villages first became established in the area. It is clearly mentioned that Ama Yangri Gompa (Monastry) was first Gompa in the Helambu area and afterward Pema Chholin Gompa (present Tarkeghyang monastry) was built by Lamas.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHistory mentions that <strong>Tarkeyghyang</strong> was established with eighty families with Meme Surya। Meme who was big Lama and to get teaching from him surrounding <strong>Hyolmo</strong> \"Barus\'\' (Baru refers rich people in Hyolmo Language) migrated to <strong>Tarkeyghyang</strong>. That\'s how huge village in <strong>Hyolmo Tarkeyghyang</strong> established which is also known as <strong>Langragyapsa</strong>.', 'Helambu Cultural Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '801-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 10:51:39', '2019-01-03 10:51:39', '', 801, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/801-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1070, 1, '2019-01-03 08:31:49', '2019-01-03 08:31:49', 'Helambu Circuit is relatively a low altitude trek in Nepal, starting with a short drive from Kathmandu to Sundarijal and then trek to Chisapani (2150 m) on along the Shivapuri ridge. You walk below 3000m through temperature forests, green valleys and experience the Yalmo culture of high mountain villages. Sweeping views of Langtang Lirung, Dorje Lakpa, Gaurishankar, Ganesh Himal, Yala Peak and plenty of other peaks from Shivapuri ridge lures every mountain lovers. The highest point of the trek is 3600m at Tharepati La pass .The trail is snow-covered in winter and in spring rhododendron forests, a variety of wild flowers and distant horizons of snowy Peaks grace the trail, making you feel as if you are in Paradise. The entire Helambu region is surprisingly pollution-free, peaceful and captivating.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAmong the delightful villages in Helambu region, Tarke Gyang and Sermathang are worth visiting as there are some very old Gompas (monasteries). You can also see the sunrise over the Himalayas from Sermathang and the sunset, when seen from there, is quite mesmerizing as well.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong> <strong> </strong>', 'Helambu Cultural Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '801-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:31:49', '2019-01-03 08:31:49', '', 801, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/801-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1071, 1, '2019-01-03 08:34:28', '2019-01-03 08:34:28', '<strong>Overview</strong>\r\n<strong>Everest Panorama Trekking</strong> as compared to other trekking routes of Everest Region is relatively easy and short but still it is very spectacular. It takes you to introduce Sherpa’s villages and its culture with great views of world’s highest mountains including Mt. Everest (8,848 m) and many other mountains.\r\n<strong>Everest View Trekking</strong> starts with a half an hour flight from Kathmandu to Lukla 2,840 m). After you get down at Lukla airstrip you’re trekking starts heading to Phakdingma, the first overnight place, following Dudha Koshi River. Next day you walk through forest of rhododendron and magnolia and arrive at Namche Bazaar, a bustling Bazaar (market) and a junction for trekkers. You stay one more extra day at Namche Bazaar for acclimatization and excursion around Khumjung village.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Trekking</strong> On that day you hike to Syangboche, one of the major spots for the view of Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Mt. Thamserku (6,608 m), Mt. Kangtega (6,685 m), Cholatse Peak (6,335 m), Taboche Peak (6,367 m) and Kwangde Peak (6,168 m) etc. Then, you walk Everest view hotel and trek down to Khumjung village, a typical Sherpa’s village. Sherpa are ethnic people of mountain region. Lots of the renowned climbers belong to this community. In Khumjung you meet local people, see their lifestyle. Visiting Khumjung Monastery makes your walking more worthwhile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Panorama Trekking</strong> Next day you are continue trekking to Thame village where Sherpa’s are ethnic peoples of Mt. Everest region. Lots of the world renowned climbers such as <strong>Mr. Tenzing Norgay Sherpa and Mr. Apa Sherpa</strong> made his 21st Mt. Everest summited and many other climbers belong to this ethnic community Mr. Tenzing Sherpa, the first climber to <strong>Mt. Everest (8,848 m)</strong> was born in this village. In Thame we will visit Thame Monastery and Stupas (Chortens) you will meet Buddhist monks in Thame and Tengboche Monastery which is considered the popular Buddhist Monastery Everest region. After the Thame Village our trekking continues to <strong>Tengboche</strong> where a famous Sherpa’s Buddhist Monastery is located. In <strong>Tengboche</strong> you will meet Buddhist monks and see their daily rituals inside the Monastery. Tengboche is the final destination of<strong> Everest Panorama Trekking</strong>. From here you return to Lukla airport via Namche Bazaar and take a flight back to Kathmandu.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Panorama Trek</strong> is ideal for older, family with children those people who desire to see world’s high mountains including Mt. Everest (8,848 m) including other many Buddhist Monasteries and Stupas (Chortens) within short days. Everest Panorama Trekking is also known by Everest View Trekking following the same itinerary and duration. This is a real holiday trekking you will never forget in your lifetime.', 'Everest Panorama Trek', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '146-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:34:28', '2019-01-03 08:34:28', '', 146, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/146-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1072, 1, '2019-01-03 08:36:08', '2019-01-03 08:36:08', '<strong>Everest Base Camp Trekking</strong> is one of the most adventurous and exciting treks that take you to the base of Mt. Everest - the world’s highest mountain. This trekking has been listed as “World’s Best Hikes out of 20 Dream Trails” by National Geographic.\r\n\r\nThe mountain scenery of the <strong>Everest region</strong> is incredibly beautiful. You will walk through multi-hued prayer flags, prayer wheels and intricately carved Mani stones dotted every hilltop and rock walls and trailside singing prayers to the gods with every breeze and every passing trekker’s. <strong>Trekking to Everest Base Camp,</strong> You can see prayer flags fluttering in the air either at the trail side or nearby Sherpa villages.\r\n\r\nWhile on the trek you will also experience Sherpa culture, their traditional lifestyle and hospitality. You will stop at numerous teahouses, sip a glass of sweetened tea with butter and salt or Chang (millet beer) and get a taste of hospitality of the Sherpa community. You will also visit Sherpa Museum at Namche Bazaar, Buddhist Monasteries and Stupas (Chortens) on the way and learn about how Lamaistic Buddhism influences Sherpa’s life.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Base Camp Trekking </strong>begins with an exciting flight to <strong>Lukla at 2,840 </strong>meters and then you walk through the picturesque Sherpa’s villages from <strong>Phakdingma (2,610 m) </strong>to<strong> Gorakshep (5,140 m) </strong>via<strong> Namche Bazaar, </strong>eventually culminating in the \"ascent\" of<strong> Kala Pattar (5,545 m).</strong> From Kala Pattar, the highest point of the trek, you will enjoy classic views of Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), Mt. Nuptse (7,861 m) Mt. Makalu (8,463 m), Mt Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Mt. Pumori 7,165 m), Mt. Kangtega (6,685 m), Mt. Thamserku (6,608 m), Cholatse Peak (6,335 m), and enjoy many other Peaks.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Base Camp Trekk </strong>most of the time you will walk above altitudes of (3,000) meters in the Khumbu and Imja valleys, whose skylines are dominated by the massive Peaks of the Eastern Himalayas. In April- May the Rhododendrons are seen in full blooming with orchids growing all along the trails in and around the <strong>Sagarmatha National Park.</strong>\r\n\r\nTrekking to Everest Base Camp does not require you to be an athlete or experienced hiker and climber. Anyone in good physical fitness and who exercises on a regular basis can comfortably and safely complete this trekking. However, you have to make difficult and sometimes long days walking to Base Camp and hiking up Kala Pattar but you have to make a slow and steady pace of walk.', 'Everest Base Camp Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '123-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:36:08', '2019-01-03 08:36:08', '', 123, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/123-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1073, 1, '2019-01-03 08:37:32', '2019-01-03 08:37:32', '<strong>Gokyo Lake - Renjo La Pass trekking</strong> is undoubtedly one of the most popular and adventurous one as compared to other normal trekking routes of the Everest region. On this trek you will explore the beautiful <strong>Gokyo Lake</strong>, <strong>Gokyo valley, Gyazumba Glacier</strong> and <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m)</strong> in the upper Khumbu valley. From the top of <strong>Gokyo Ri (5,369 m)</strong> you will enjoy more distinct and closer view of the world\'s highest peak, Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), the 6th highest peak, Mt. Cho Oyu (8,201m), Mt. Makalu (8463 m), Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m) and many other snow-clad Himalayan peaks from east to west.\r\n\r\n<strong>Gokyo Lake - Renjo La Pass trekking</strong> after <strong>Gokyo Lake</strong> you will continue a long day trekking and cross over the <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m).</strong> From the top of the Pass you will enjoy the stunning views you can see full of Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), Mt. Makalu (8,463 m), Cholatse Peak (6335 m) and Taboche Peak (6,367 m) much beautiful views from the top of <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m).</strong> Much similar to that from Gokyo Ri. Besides, you will also enjoy the great view of the Gokyo Lake with Mt. Everest on one side and Relama Lake on the other side.\r\n\r\nOn this trekking you follow the route through route Lukla, Phakdingma, Namche Bazaar – Khumjung Monastery, Phortse Tanga, Machhermo, Gokyo Lake, cross of <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m),</strong> Lungden, Thame, Namche Bazaar, Lukla and fly back to Kathmandu. While heading for <strong>Gokyo Lake with Renjo La Pass</strong> you will spend one extra day at Namche Bazaar for acclimatization and at the same you will enjoy excursion around Sherpa’s villages, Museum, Buddhist Stupas, Monasteries, and beautiful sights of Himalayan Mountain Range. On the rest day at Namche Bazaar you will make excursion to <strong>Khumjung village</strong>, a typical Sherpa village.\r\n\r\nSherpa’s are ethnic people of mountain region. Lots of the renowned climbers belong to this community. At <strong>Khumjung </strong>you will meet local people and experience their culture and lifestyle. Visiting <strong>Khumjung Monastery</strong> makes your excursion more worthwhile. At the same time you will visit Thame village where a famous Sherpa and Buddhist Monastery is located. In Thame Monastery you will meet Buddhist monks and see their daily rituals.\r\n\r\nGokyo Lake - Renjo La Pass trek can be organized on any day of the week during the months of March through May and September through November for minimum group size of 2 and maximum 19 people. High Mountain Himalaya Treks &amp; Expedition Pvt. Ltd. provides a reliable, friendly and knowledgeable English, Russain and Japanese speaking trekking guide and porters with all necessary permits. Please contact us for further details at <a href=\"mailto:info@highhimalayatreks.com\">info@highhimalayatreks.com</a>', 'Gokyo Lake - Renjo La Pass Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '159-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:37:32', '2019-01-03 08:37:32', '', 159, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/159-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1074, 1, '2019-01-03 08:38:50', '2019-01-03 08:38:50', '<strong>Gokyo Lake - Chola Pass &amp; Everest Base Camp Trekking</strong> is one of the most adventurous and challenging trek in the Everest Region. It follows the route via high pass called Chola Pass at 5,420 meters into Mt. Everest Base Camp (5,364 m). <strong>Trekking to Gokyo Lake - Chola Pass &amp; Everest Base Camp</strong> begins with an amazing flight to <strong>Lukla.</strong> From <strong>Lukla</strong> you will walk uphill slowly following the trail to the Dudh Kosi (it means ‘River of Milk’), and all through forests of Rhododendron, pine and magnolia. After few hours of trekking you will eventually reach Namche Bazaar (3,340 m) and spend one more day at Namche Bazaar (the delightful Sherpa capital) for acclimatization and optional hike around. From Namche you will visit other Sherpa villages such as Phortse Tanga and Machhermo before heading for Gokyo Lake.\r\n\r\n<strong>Trekking to Gokyo Lake - Chola Pass &amp; Everest Base Camp </strong>after you reach Gokyo Lake you climb Gokyo Ri (5369m.) and from the top of Gokyo Ri you will enjoy stunning peaks of different mountains such as Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), Mt. Makalu (8,463 m), Mt. Cho Oyu (8,201 m), Mt Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Mt. Kangtega (6,685 m), Mt. Thamserku (6,608 m), Cholatse Peak (6335 m), Taboche Peak (6,367 m) and many others. Then, next day you cross Cho La Pass (5,420 m) and reach at Dzongla.\r\n\r\nAfter Dzongla you move towards Gorakshep and ascend to Kala Pattar (5,545 m) from Kala Pattar you will enjoy an impressive up-close view of Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), Mt. Nuptse (7861 m) Mt. Makalu (8,463 m), Mt Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Mt. Pumori 7,165 m), Mt. Kangtega (6,685 m), Mt. Thamserku (6,608 m), Cholatse Peak (6,335 m), and enjoy many other Peaks.\r\n\r\nThen, next day morning you trek to Mt. Everest Base Camp. When you return from <strong>Everest Base Camp (5,364 m) </strong>you follow the route through Pangboche, Tengboche and <strong>Namche Bazaar. </strong>While on trek you will enjoy the incredible mountain scenery until you reach Lukla airstrip. Next day morning you take a flight back to Kathmandu.\r\n\r\n<strong>Gokyo - Chola Pass &amp; Everest Base Camp Trekking</strong> is popular for every traveler and group alike. It gives a complete scenario of different flora and fauna, rural lifestyle of the Sherpa people, Buddhism, Monasteries, Stupas (Chortens) and other spectacular Mountain scenery.', 'Gokyo Lake - Chola Pass & Everest Base Camp Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:38:50', '2019-01-03 08:38:50', '', 172, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1075, 1, '2019-01-03 08:40:21', '2019-01-03 08:40:21', '<strong>Everest Two High Passes </strong><strong>Trekking</strong> is undoubtedly one of the most popular and adventurous trek comparatively to other normal trekking routes in the Everest region. You will cross over <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m)</strong> and explore the beautiful Gokyo valley and Gokyo Lake in the upper Khumbu valley. From the top of <strong>Gokyo RI (5,369 m)</strong> you will enjoy more distinct and closer view of the world\'s highest peak, Mt. Everest (8,848 m), Mt. Lhotse (8,516 m), the 6th highest peak, Mt. Cho Oyu (8,201 m), Mt. Makalu (8,463 m) Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m) and many other snow-clad peaks of Everest region.\r\n\r\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass – Everest Base Camp Trekking</strong> after Gokyo Lake you will continue a long day trekking and cross over the <strong>Cho La Pass (5,420 m) </strong>and it takes about 9 hrs. Now you ascend slightly along the valley towards Cho La Pass. The Pass you can pass through is covered with rocks. While crossing the <strong>Cho La Pass </strong>is most of the time covered with blue Ice giving you a chill feeling. Here you can also, enjoy the stunning Panorama views of Lobuche Peak (6,119 m), Mt. Ama Dablam (6,812 m), Cholatse Peak (6,335 m) From Thagnag way crossing the<strong> Cho La Pass (5,420 m)</strong> the trail descends steeply down for an hour and then slightly descends all the way to Dzongla.\r\n\r\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass - Everest Trekking</strong> we follow the route Namche Bazaar- Thame Lungden, cross <strong>Renjo La Pass (5,369 m),</strong> Gokyo Lake, Thagnag,<strong> Cho La Pass (5,420 m),</strong> Dzongla, Lobuche, Gorakshep, <strong>Everest Base Camp (5,364 m)</strong>, <strong>Kala Pattar (5,545 m),</strong> Dingboche, Tengboche, Namche Bazaar, Lukla and fly back to Kathmandu. While heading for Renjo La Pass and Gokyo valley you will spend one extra day at Namche Bazaar for acclimatization excursion around Khumjung village.\r\n\r\n<strong>Renjo La Pass - Gokyo Lake - Cho La Pass - Everest Trekking </strong>On the same day you will enjoy excursion around Sherpa’s villages, museum and many Buddhist Monastery and Stupas in Phakdingma, Namche Bazaar, Thame, Dingbocchce, Pangboche, Tengboche and Khumjung Buddhist monasteries Khumbu valley, and immerse in the beautiful sights of Himalayan Mountain range. At Khumjung village you will encounter the local people and experience their culture and tradition. Lots of renowned climbers of Nepal belong to Sherpa’s community from upper every Himalaya Valley. Visiting Khumjung Thame and Tengboche Monasteries makes your excursion more worthwhile.\r\n\r\n<strong>Everest Two High Passes </strong><strong>Trekking</strong> at the same time you will visit Tengboche where a famous Sherpa’s Buddhist Monastery is located. In Thame and Tengboche monasteries you will meet Buddhist monks and see their daily rituals. This is long trek with many cultural and natural highlights and recommendable only to those trekkers who are keen to walk at higher altitude for longer days.', 'Everest Two High Passes Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '52-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:40:21', '2019-01-03 08:40:21', '', 52, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/52-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1076, 1, '2019-01-03 08:43:55', '2019-01-03 08:43:55', '<strong>Island Peak is one</strong><strong> of the most popular trekking peaks in Nepal\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Island Peak (6160m) Climbing</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Island Peak </strong>also locally known as (Imja Tse) is the most popular trekking peak situated in the Everest region in Nepal. The name itself suggests that this peak looks like an Island being surrounded in a sea of ice when we view from Dingboche. The climbing trip to Island Peak starts with an exhilarating mountain flight to Lukla airstrip.\r\n\r\nFrom Lukla we ascend slowly to northward, through Namche Bazaar and finally reach the Island Peak Base Camp on the eleventh day where we prepare for next day climbing. The summit day begins very early morning with an interesting scramble along a rock ridge to a glacier. Above the rock ridge there is a steep snow head wall that leads straight to the summit. To step foot on the top of the peak is physically challenging but it would be a great day of achievement for climbers.\r\n\r\nThe summit of Island Peak looks very attractive with a highly glaciated west face rising from the Lhotse Glacier. The ridge rising to the south leads to the summit of Island Peak. The extension of this ridge to the southwest is the part of the normal route of ascent and leads to the South Summit.  One can enjoy the amazing views of Mount Ama Dablam, Makalu, Lhotse Shar and many other mountains. Lhotse from  the summit. However, before attempting this climb, climbers are advised to acclimatize by trekking to Everest Base camp.\r\n\r\nHigh Mountain Himalaya Treks and Expedition Pvt. Ltd. offers highly experienced and professional climbing Sherpa and guides to ensure safe ascent and summit along with the climbing permit and all other necessary logistics. This Island Peak Climbing package trip can be flexibly adjusted to our clients’ requirements. Safety and comfort is our priority. For further inquiry and price, please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:sherpachangia@hotmail.com\">sherpachangia@hotmail.com</a>', 'Island Peak', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '823-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:43:55', '2019-01-03 08:43:55', '', 823, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/823-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1077, 1, '2019-01-03 08:45:18', '2019-01-03 08:45:18', '<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Yala Peak (5732m) is one of Nepal\'s easier trekking peaks. Yala is a perfect peak accessible to a trekker without any climbing experience, who want to do trekking and peak climbing at the same time in Langtang region. From the summit of Yala peak the Langtang Himal as well as Shishapangma, just 20km from Yala Peak can be seen in a clear day.</span></p>\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">It takes 9hrs drive from Kathmandu to the trailhead at Syabhrubesi and then the trek begins through agricultural farmland, villages and forest of Rhododendron, conifer, bamboos, oaks and pines. During the spring the forest looks enchanting with flowers all around. The trail further follows the narrow gorge of Langtang River till it ends at the large alpine grass land of Kyanjin Gumba (3800m) where the glacier meets the meadow. You can see Yaks grazing in the meadow with the backdrops of snowy peaks of Langtang Ri, Langtang Lirung (7246m.), Dorjee Lakpa and many other unnamed mountains around you. This peak climbing trip enables you to explore the Langtang National Park, the home of Tibetan looking people-the Tamangs.</span></p>\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">After acclimatizing in Kyanjin Gumba and exploring the glacier, you hike to the Base Camp (4800m) located at the base of the Yala Peak summit. The summit climb requires only 700m of elevation gain consisting of non technical scramble with no objective danger. After trekking for 6 days you will have a solid acclimatization for safe climb to the elevation of 5500m.</span></p>\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">High Mountain Himalaya Treks offer full board package for Yala Peak climbing which includes climbing permit and all other necessary logistical support from arrival to departure. Upon your request we also customize our service up to base camp and the clients may arrange all required logistics from the base camp onward. However, our company arranges the peak permit, land transport and supporting staff.</span></p>\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Please contact us whether full board service or base camp service is required for Yala Peak Climbing. Our full board service includes airport pick up, transfer, accommodations, trekking and climbing route, hygienic high altitude food cooked freshly by our experienced cooks, experienced and professional trekking and climbing Sherpas and guides, departure transfers etc.</span></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Yala Peak Climbing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '835-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 08:45:18', '2019-01-03 08:45:18', '', 835, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/835-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
