(1090, 1, '2019-01-03 09:16:46', '2019-01-03 09:16:46', '<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Yala Peak (5732m) is one of Nepal\'s easier trekking peaks. Yala is a perfect peak accessible to a trekker without any climbing experience, who want to do trekking and peak climbing at the same time in Langtang region. From the summit of Yala peak the Langtang Himal as well as Shishapangma, just 20km from Yala Peak can be seen in a clear day.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">It takes 9hrs drive from Kathmandu to the trailhead at Syabhrubesi and then the trek begins through agricultural farmland, villages and forest of Rhododendron, conifer, bamboos, oaks and pines. During the spring the forest looks enchanting with flowers all around. The trail further follows the narrow gorge of Langtang River till it ends at the large alpine grass land of Kyanjin Gumba (3800m) where the glacier meets the meadow. You can see Yaks grazing in the meadow with the backdrops of snowy peaks of Langtang Ri, Langtang Lirung (7246m.), Dorjee Lakpa and many other unnamed mountains around you. This peak climbing trip enables you to explore the Langtang National Park, the home of Tibetan looking people-the Tamangs.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">After acclimatizing in Kyanjin Gumba and exploring the glacier, you hike to the Base Camp (4800m) located at the base of the Yala Peak summit. The summit climb requires only 700m of elevation gain consisting of non technical scramble with no objective danger. After trekking for 6 days you will have a solid acclimatization for safe climb to the elevation of 5500m.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">High Mountain Himalaya Treks offer full board package for Yala Peak climbing which includes climbing permit and all other necessary logistical support from arrival to departure. Upon your request we also customize our service up to base camp and the clients may arrange all required logistics from the base camp onward. However, our company arranges the peak permit, land transport and supporting staff.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"xmsonormal\" style=\"background: white;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma\',sans-serif; color: #212121;\">Please contact us whether full board service or base camp service is required for Yala Peak Climbing. Our full board service includes airport pick up, transfer, accommodations, trekking and climbing route, hygienic high altitude food cooked freshly by our experienced cooks, experienced and professional trekking and climbing Sherpas and guides, departure transfers etc.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Yala Peak Climbing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '835-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 09:16:46', '2019-01-03 09:16:46', '', 835, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/835-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1091, 1, '2019-01-03 09:23:02', '2019-01-03 09:23:02', 'Nepal is one of the best destinations for newly married couples. It is the land of colorful cultures, ancient history, and wilderness and has been popular getaway for honeymooners. Many couple makes their <strong>honeymoon trips</strong> <strong>to Nepal </strong>in the beginning of their conjugal life. It is not just an ordinary tour; rather it is a blend of leisure and a bit adventure suiting the couples\' interest and convenient time. Honeymoon is the most precious days for the newly married couples: it would be a time to relax, enjoy each other’s company and relieve memories of the special moments.\n\nYour first trip to Nepal as a married couple will be remarkable. Begin your life together in <strong>Kathmandu</strong>, one of the world’s most culturally rich city and sightseeing in different <strong>World Heritage Sites</strong> is an unforgettable experience.\n\nIt will be filled with fine food and fun times dictated by nothing. You will be travelling various places you’ve never heard of and showing you things you could have never imagined. Your travel will be as romantic and as boundless as your love for each other, which means your honeymoon trip can only be experienced in <strong>Himalayan country of Nepal</strong>.\n\n<strong>Nepal Honeymoon tour</strong> is especially designed, stay at one of Nepal\'s most legendary hotels, unique itineraries covering all popular places and flawless travel arrangements', 'Nepal Honeymoon Tour', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '851-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 09:23:02', '2019-01-03 09:23:02', '', 851, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/851-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
