(1098, 1, '2019-01-03 10:47:27', '2019-01-03 10:47:27', '<strong>Chitlang</strong> is a beautiful ancient village which lies in <strong>Makwanpur district</strong> on the south-west of Kathmandu valley. The original name of this village is Chitrapur. We begin our journey by road from Kathmandu to <strong>Thankot Godam</strong> and begin the trek to Chitlang via <strong>Chandragiri Hill</strong> top. We trek through <strong>Markhu Village</strong> and enjoy boating at <strong>Kulekhani</strong>. At Chitlang village we experience Newari culture and lifestyle of the people. From Chitlang village we hike its surrounding area and continue our trek as far as Chitwan National Park, lowland part of Nepal.\n\nThe <strong>picturesque Chitlang</strong> has a mild and cold climate and is surrounded by green hills. The major attraction of our trek is the Chandragiri hill located at the elevation of 2400 m. You will enjoy the splendid view of the entire <strong>Kathmandu Valley</strong> from the top of this hill. The Kulekhani Hydro Electricity Project is also worth visiting on the way to Chitlang.\n\nDuring our stay and excursion around Chitlang village you can observe the geographical diversity, flora and fauna. Most importantly the first car was brought through Chitlang village carried by local people in the Rana Regime. The village itself could be a unique destination for the visitors. The villagers are deprived of many basic amenities. With the view to up lift the socio- economic condition of the villages, it is worth to visit Chitlang village and contribute financially to boost the local economy of the people.\n\nInscriptions dating back to Lichchavi era have been found in this place, according to which, King Anshuvarma had established a settlement for shepherds of Chitlang believed to be the descendants of rulers of Gopal era. The village itself is unspoiled Tamang, Newar, Brahmin and Magar settlement set in the hilly country side at an altitude ranging from 1750 to 2000m of elevation.', 'Chitlang Village Cultural Trekking', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '803-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 10:47:27', '2019-01-03 10:47:27', '', 803, 'http://highhimalayatreks.com/demo/803-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
